(136, 'To Find this Guide:', 'Go to home.drew.edu.<br />\nSelect&nbsp;<em><strong>Research Resources</strong></em><strong>&nbsp;</strong>under <b><i>Library</i></b><br />\nUnder&nbsp;<strong><em>Subject Databases</em></strong> in the center column, click on&nbsp;<strong><em>List of Resources by Subject Area.</em></strong><br />\nScroll down to&nbsp;<em><strong>Summer College: Avian Flu</strong></em>', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(137, 'Picking Keywords', 'When searching in academic sources, you&#39;ll need to think of the terms that might be used to describe your subject.\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Avian Influenza</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>H5N1</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>Bird Flu</strong></li>\n</ul>\nAdditional concept terms:\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li><strong>pandemic</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>documentary</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>&quot;Micah Fink&quot;</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>bioweapon</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>ferret</strong></li>\n	<li><strong>ethics</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<br />\nPhrases should be in quotes: &quot;Avian Influenza&quot; &quot;Bird flu&quot;<br />\n<br />\nYou can combine terms that mean the same thing with OR:<br />\n&quot;Avian Influenza&quot; OR &quot;Bird Flu&quot; OR H5N1<br />\n<br />\nIf you have two concepts such as Bird Flu and Bioweapon, you can use AND to combine them:<br />\n&quot;Bird Flu&quot; AND bioweapon<br />\nto be sure you get both.', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(139, 'Search Academic Search Premier', '1. &nbsp;Enter your terms in the search boxes.\n<ul>\n	<li>Phrases of two or more words should be in quotation marks: &nbsp;<em>&quot;Avian Influenza&quot; &nbsp;&quot;Bird Flu&quot;</em></li>\n	<li>If there are two or more&nbsp;terms for a concept, enter both, separated with OR: &nbsp;<em>&quot;Avian Influenza&quot;&nbsp;OR &quot;Bird Flu&quot; OR H5N1</em></li>\n	<li>You can add&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jheise/flu2..png" style="width: 688px; height: 718px;" /><br />\n2. &nbsp;To retrieve ONLY academic articles, click <i>Scholarly (Peer Reviewed) Journals</i>.<br />\n3. &nbsp;If the full text is not supplied in the database, click&nbsp;<em>Search for Article</em> to see if it&#39;s available elsewhere through the Library&#39;s resources.', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
