(217, 'Citation help', '<strong style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Web resources for citation help</strong><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">{{dab},{316}, {MLA Formatting and Style Guide &ndash; The OWL at Purdue},{11}}</span><br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1125}, {Annotated Bibliographies - The OWL at Purdue},{11}}<br />\n<br />\n<strong style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Electronic citation managment</strong><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">{{dab},{1045}, {EndnoteWeb},{11}}</span><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">(Beware: No citation software is perfect--check your work!) &nbsp;</span><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Endnote+Web+Bibliographic+Software" style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" target="_blank">Instructions for EndNote Web</a><br />\n<br />\n<strong>Books shelved near Research Help Desk.</strong><br />\nGibaldi, Joseph.&nbsp;MLA Style Manual and Guide to Scholarly Publishing. New York: Modern Language Association of America, 2008. Print.&nbsp;PN147 .G444 2008<br />\n<br />\nGibaldi, Joseph, and Modern Language Association of America.&nbsp;MLA Handbook for Writers of Research Papers. New York: Modern Language Association of America, 2009. Print.LB2369 .G53 2009<br />\n<br />\n<strong style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Reference Books (Located on C Level of library)</strong><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">Lipson, Charles.&nbsp;</span><i style="font-size: 13px; zoom: 1; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">Doing 