xt-decoration: none;">Macmillan</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="http://www.oxfordreference.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/browse?avail_0=lib&amp;btog=book&amp;pageSize=100&amp;sort=title&amp;t1=ORO:AHU03020" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Oxford&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>Concordances, e.g.&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="http://www.eliyah.com/lexicon.html" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Strong&#39;s</a></li>\n	<li>Interlinear Bibles\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li><em>NIV Interlinear Hebrew-English Old Testament</em>&nbsp;[Ref. BS715]</li>\n		<li><em>New Greek-English Interlinear New Testament</em>&nbsp;[BS1965.5]</li>\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://biblehub.com/interlinear/" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Online interlinear Bible</a></li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>Lexicons and word studies\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li><em>Greek English Lexicon of the New Testament&nbsp;</em>(BDAG) (Ref. PA881 .B38)</li>\n		<li>Brown Driver Briggs,&nbsp;<em>Hebrew and English Lexicon</em>&nbsp;(BDB) (Ref. PJ4833 .B67)</li>\n		<li><em>Theological Dictionary of the New Testament</em>&nbsp;[Kittel] [Ref BS2312 .K5813]</li>\n		<li><em>Theological&nbsp;Dictionary of the Old Testament&nbsp;</em>[Ref. BS440 .B5713]</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>Commentaries\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li><em>New Testament Commentary Survey</em>, 6th&nbsp;ed., 2007 [BS2341.2 .C33]</li>\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://site.ebrary.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/lib/drew/docDetail.action?docID=10682447" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;"><em>Old Testament Commentary&nbsp;Survey</em></a>, 5th ed., 2013</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>Interpretive methods\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li><em>Dictionary of Biblical Interpretation</em>,1999 [Ref. BS500 .D5]</li>\n		<li><em>Handbook of Postmodern Biblical Interpretation,</em>&nbsp;2000 [Ref. BS476 .H36]</li>\n		<li>And see&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/download/attachments/23304382/nt.pdf?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1376491444371" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">chapters</a>&nbsp;on methods in&nbsp;<em>The Blackwell Companion to the New Testament&nbsp;</em>[BS2330.3 B63]</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>Bibliography\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.oxfordbibliographies.com/browse?module_0=obo-9780195393361" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Oxford Bibliographies Online: Biblical Studies&nbsp;&nbsp;</a></li>\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://jot.sagepub.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/content/36/5.toc" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Book List</a>&nbsp;of&nbsp;<em>Journal for the Study of the Old Testament</em></li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Key journals</strong></p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>Bible and Critical Theory</em>&nbsp;[<a data-mce-="" href="http://bibleandcriticaltheory.org/index.php/bct/index" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">online&nbsp;</a>only]</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>Journal of Biblical Literature</em></li>\n	<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>Journal for the Study of the New Testament</em></li>\n	<li><em>&nbsp;</em><em>New Testament Studies</em></li>\n	<li>&nbsp; Finding others in the&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="https://librarycat.drew.edu/" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">catalog</a>&nbsp;[using subheading: --Periodicals]</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Library catalogs</strong>:&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="https://librarycat.drew.edu/" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Drew</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="http://newfirstsearch.oclc.org.ezproxy.drew.edu/WebZ/FSPrefs?entityjsdetect=:javascript=true:screensize=large:sessionid=fsapp2-58246-hm3jossf-ek5hlc:entitypagenum=1:0" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Worldcat</a></p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>Authority term vs. keyword\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li>Bible N T Mark xvi</li>\n		<li>Mark-16</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://books.google.com/books?id=IbuBa8Qy3AwC&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;dq=intitle:genesis+inauthor:rad&amp;hl=en&amp;ei=gFuXTPKaO8L98AaElMWNDA&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;ct=result&amp;resnum=1&amp;ved=0CDAQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Commentaries</a>&nbsp;vs.&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="http://books.google.com/books?id=XyzNO-Om2DwC&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;dq=intitle:forsaken+intitle:first-born&amp;hl=en&amp;ei=RluXTMblOcL68AahvtWMDA&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;ct=result&amp;resnum=1&amp;ved=0CCwQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&amp;q&amp;f=false" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">monographs</a></li>\n	<li>Biblical history [e.g. Bible History of Biblical events]</li>\n	<li>Social background [e.g. Poor Biblical teaching]</li>\n	<li>Interpretive methods [e.g. Bible postcolonial criticism]</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Periodical Databases</strong></p>\n\n<ul >\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://web.ebscohost.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/ehost/search/advanced?sid=7fd056ed-7912-4977-9160-c269c7eaa980%40sessionmgr10&amp;vid=1&amp;hid=25" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">ATLA</a></li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://web.ebscohost.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/ehost/search/advanced?sid=2f7f60e7-ed1b-40ff-b935-776f92a752b7%40sessionmgr198&amp;vid=1&amp;hid=112" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">OT Abstracts</a></li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://web.ebscohost.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/ehost/search/advanced?sid=f2e83e61-dbc5-4d53-acc3-896a2de7a441%40sessionmgr112&amp;vid=1&amp;hid=112" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">NT Abstracts</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Electronic Bibles</strong></p>\n\n<ul >\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://unbound.biola.edu/" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Unbound Bible</a></li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/electronic-resources-by-title" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">TLG</a></li>\n	<li>BibleWorks\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/BibleWorks+Tipsheet" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Drew tip sheet</a></li>\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.library.yale.edu/div/bibleworks.html" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Some help from Yale Divinity School&nbsp;</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Websites</strong></p>\n\n<ul >\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.ntgateway.com/" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">New Testament Gateway</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://otgateway.com/" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Old Testament Gateway&nbsp;</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.wabashcenter.wabash.edu/resources/guide_headings.aspx" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Wabash Center</a>&nbsp;[for Biblical studies sites]</li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL);
INSERT INTO `pluslet` (`pluslet_id`, `title`, `body`, `local_file`, `clone`, `type`, `extra`, `hide_titlebar`, `collapse_body`, `titlebar_styling`) VALUES
(229, 'Historical Studies', '<p style="margin: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><a data-mce-="" href="https://librarycat.drew.edu/" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Catalog</a><br />\n<a data-mce-="" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/databases-by-title-a-z" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Databases</a></p>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Introduction to historical research</strong></p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>Bradley, James E. and Richard A Muller.&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>Church History: An Introduction to Research</em><em>, Reference Works, and Methods.</em>&nbsp;Grand Rapids: Eerdmans, 1995 [Ref. 270.072 B811c]</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>History and the other Areas</strong></p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.degruyter.com/view/db/ebr?format=ONKO" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;"><em>Encyclopedia of the Bible and its Reception</em>&nbsp;</a>[Ref. BS440 .E539]</li>\n	<li><em><a data-mce-="" href="http://go.galegroup.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/ps/displayAllBooksForSubject?subject=History&amp;inPS=true&amp;prodId=GVRL&amp;userGroupName=madi95127" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">New Dictionary of the History of Ideas</a></em></li>\n	<li>The Lives of Great Religious Books (series from Princeton) (<a data-mce-="" href="http://site.ebrary.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/lib/drew/docDetail.action?docID=10533601" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">example</a>)</li>\n	<li>Danto, Elizabeth Ann.&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>Historical Research.&nbsp;</em>&nbsp;Pocket Guides to Social Work Research Methods.&nbsp; New York: Oxford University Press, 2008. [Ref. HM 571 .D36]</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Primary vs Secondary sources</strong>&nbsp;(from Bradley and Muller, above)</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>Primary source: &quot;A document, datum, or artifact that belongs to the era under examination and that offers the most direct access to the person or issues being studied,&quot; p. 39.</li>\n	<li>Secondary sources: &quot;Offer information about an event but stand removed from it either in time or by a process of transmission of information,&quot; p. 41.&nbsp;<em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Critical editions</strong></p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>In the works of antiquity and Middle Ages\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li><em>Corpus Christianorum: Series Latina/Graeca</em></li>\n		<li><em>Corpus Scriptorum Ecclesiasticorum Latinorum</em></li>\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://stephanus.tlg.uci.edu.ezproxy.drew.edu/inst/fontsel" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Thesaurus Linguae Gracae</a></li>\n		<li>Consult the &quot;Clavis&quot; volumes in the Corpus Christianorum series for guidance to critical editions of biblical and medieval apocyrypha &amp; pseudepigrapha, and the Greek and Latin fathers [Search the&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="https://librarycat.drew.edu/" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">catalog</a>&nbsp;with the key words Corpus and Clavis to turn these up]</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>In American religious history, e.g....\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li><em>The Works of Jonathan Edwards&nbsp;</em>(Yale)&nbsp;[BX7117 .E3; see esp. v. 1, &quot;<a data-mce-="" href="http://edwards.yale.edu/archive?path=aHR0cDovL2Vkd2FyZHMueWFsZS5lZHUvY2dpLWJpbi9uZXdwaGlsby9uYXZpZ2F0ZS5wbD93amVvLjA=" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Note on the text</a>,&quot; p. 118]</li>\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://whiteheadresearch.org/occasions/news/2010-09-11-Inauguration_of_CEW.shtml" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">The Whitehead Research Project</a></li>\n		<li><em>The Works of George Santayana&nbsp;</em>(MIT) [see especially catalog record,&nbsp;<em>The Last Puritan</em>]</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Translations</strong>&nbsp;(Patristics, Medieval Studies)</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>Guides to choosing\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li>Bibliographies in&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="http://go.galegroup.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/ps/infomark.do?action=interpret&amp;source=library&amp;actionString=DO_DISPLAY_ABOUT_PAGE&amp;tabID=T002&amp;prodId=GVRL&amp;userGroupName=madi95127&amp;docId=CX3424599999&amp;type=aboutBook&amp;version=1.0&amp;authCount=1&amp;u=madi95127" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Encyclopedia of Religion&nbsp;</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n		<li>Essays in The Cambridge&nbsp;Companion to .... [e.g. Augustine, Dante, etc]</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>Examples in series\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li>Loeb Classical Library [Philo, Josephus, Clement, Tertullian, Augustine, etc]&nbsp;</li>\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.ccel.org/fathers.html" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Ante-Nicene&nbsp;Fathers; Nicene and Post-Nicene Fathers</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n		<li>Fathers of the&nbsp;Church (CUA Press) [Clement, Tertullian, Augustine, etc]</li>\n		<li>Classics of Western Spirituality [Origen, Augustine, Hildegard, Julien, etc]</li>\n		<li>Library of Christian Classics [Clement, Origen, Augustine, Aquinas, Luther, etc)</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Online primary sources fulltext</strong></p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.ccel.org/" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Christian Classics Ethereal Library</a></li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://stephanus.tlg.uci.edu.ezproxy.drew.edu/inst/fontsel" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Thesaurus Linguae Graecae</a></li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.roger-pearse.com/weblog/patrologia-latina-pl-volumes-available-online/" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Patrologia Latina</a>&nbsp;[also in print, with Patrologia Graeca: 281.1 M635; NB: these are not critical editions]</li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://clt.brepolis.net.ezproxy.drew.edu/emgh/pages/Search.aspx" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Monumenta Germaniae Historica</a>&nbsp;(MGH)</li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://books.google.com/bkshp?hl=en&amp;tab=wp" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Google Books</a></li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.accessible.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/accessible/preLog" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">African American Newspapers: The 19th Century</a></li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://infoweb.newsbank.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/iw-search/we/HistArchive?p_product=EANX&amp;p_action=timeframes&amp;p_theme=ahnp&amp;p_nbid=H67K59GRMTMxMTI2NzAyNS42ODI5NDY6MToxMzoxOTIuMTA3LjM5LjE5&amp;p_clear_search=yes&amp;d_refprod=EANX&amp;" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">America&#39;s Historical Newspapers</a></li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://proquest.umi.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/login?COPT=REJTPTFhY2QmSU5UPTAmVkVSPTI=&amp;clientId=10355" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">New York Times Historical</a></li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.lexisnexis.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/hottopics/lnacademic/" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">LexisNexis</a></li>\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://go.galegroup.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/ps/displayAllBooksForSubject?subject=History&amp;inPS=true&amp;prodId=GVRL&amp;userGroupName=madi95127" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">American Decades: Primary Sources</a></li>\n	<li>And see:&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/American+History-+Primary+Sources+Online" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">American History: Primary Sources Online</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Encyclopedias</strong></p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.drew.edu/depts/library/er-subject.aspx?category=E-Reference%20Books" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Online</a>\n\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.oxfordreference.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/view/10.1093/acref/9780192802903.001.0001/acref-9780192802903?rskey=rtgIoD&amp;result=13&amp;q=" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Oxford Dictionary of the Christian Church</a>&nbsp;[Ref BR95 .O8]</li>\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.oxfordreference.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/view/10.1093/acref/9780195064933.001.0001/acref-9780195064933?rskey=nLLzIG&amp;result=38&amp;q=" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Oxford Encyclopedia of the Reformation</a>&nbsp;[Ref BR302.8 .O93 ]</li>\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://library.cqpress.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/era/?PHPSESSID=6bs7ra0rfb15dc90feitlf9af2" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Encyclopedia of Religion in America</a>&nbsp;[Ref. B2520 E52]</li>\n		<li><em>New Catholic Encyclopedia</em>, 1st and 2nd eds, 1967 and 2003 [Ref BX841 .N44;&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="http://go.galegroup.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/ps/displayAllBooksForSubject?subject=Religion&amp;inPS=true&amp;prodId=GVRL&amp;userGroupName=madi95127" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">online</a>]</li>\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.oxfordreference.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/view/10.1093/acref/9780227679319.001.0001/acref-9780227679319" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Encyclopedia of the Middle Ages</a>&nbsp;(e.g.&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="http://www.oxfordreference.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/view/10.1093/acref/9780227679319.001.0001/acref-9780227679319-e-2290?rskey=AIwUww&amp;result=2" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Poverty</a>)</li>\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://knowledge.sagepub.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/view/worldpoverty/SAGE.xml" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Encyclopedia of World Poverty</a>&nbsp;(e.g.&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="http://knowledge.sagepub.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/view/worldpoverty/n319.xml" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">History of Poverty</a>)</li>\n		<li><a data-mce-="" href="http://www.history.salempress.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166