(269, 'Session 5: Humanities Resources for Theo Stud', '<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Theological studies are&nbsp;<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/download/attachments/23304368/Holidaywindow1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1315400123911%3E" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">interdisciplinary</a><br />\n&quot;For God&#39;s sake, why bring God into everything?&quot; --Evelyn Waugh,<a class="external-link" href="http://www.amazon.com/Brideshead-Revisited-Evelyn-Waugh/dp/0316216453/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1402672749&amp;sr=1-1&amp;keywords=brideshead+revisited" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">&nbsp;<em>Brideshead Revisited</em></a></p>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Philosophy</strong><br />\n&quot;See to it that no one makes a prey of you by philosophy and empty deceit&quot; (Colossians 2:8)<br />\nWhy Philosophy?:&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="https://selfservice.drew.edu/prod/bwckctlg.p_display_courses?term_in=201510&amp;one_subj=TPHL&amp;sel_crse_strt=500&amp;sel_crse_end=500&amp;sel_subj=&amp;sel_levl=&amp;sel_schd=&amp;sel_coll=&amp;sel_divs=&amp;sel_dept=&amp;sel_attr=" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">TPHL500</a></p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>Key reference sources\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li>&nbsp;{{dab},{194}, {Routledge Encyclopedia of Philosophy},{00}}</li>\n		<li>&nbsp;{{dab},{195}, {Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy},{00}}</li>\n		<li>&nbsp;{{dab},{895}, {New Dictionary of the History of Ideas},{00}}&nbsp;(click on G for Gale Virtual Reference Library)</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>Key database:&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/databases-by-title-a-z" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">&nbsp;</a>{{dab},{93}, {Philosopher&#39;s Index},{00}}(see under P)</li>\n	<li>Helpful websites:&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/subject-databases" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Databases by subject&nbsp;</a>(scroll down to Philosophy) and&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/resourcetype/philosophysites" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">another listing</a></li>\n	<li>Making sense of difficult philosophers\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li>Routledge Critical Thinkers: Bhabha, Derrida, Levinas, Spivak, Zizek....</li>\n		<li>Guides for the Perplexed (Continuum): Plato, Aristotle, Spinoza,&nbsp;Heidegger...</li>\n		<li>(finding books in series: use &quot;Exact&quot; search in the<a class="external-link" href="https://librarycat.drew.edu/web2/tramp2.exe/log_in/guest?SETTING_KEY=English" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">&nbsp;catalog</a>)</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>History</strong><br />\nA key distinction:</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>Primary source: &quot;A document, datum, or artifact that belongs to the era under examination and that offers the most direct access<br />\n	to the person or issues being studied.&quot;<br />\n	--James Bradley and Richard Muller,&nbsp;<em>Church History: An Introduction to Research, Reference Works, and Methods</em>&nbsp;(Grand Rapids, Mich: Eerdmans, 1995), 39</li>\n	<li><em>Secondary sources: &quot;Offer information about an event but stand removed from it either in time or by a process of transmission of information.&quot; Ibid., 41.</em></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Key reference sources</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>&nbsp;Online&nbsp;\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li>&nbsp;{{dab},{190}, {Oxford Dictionary of the Christian Church},{00}}&nbsp;[Ref BR95 .O8]</li>\n		<li><em>&nbsp;</em>{{dab},{942}, {Encyclopedia of Ancient History},{00}}</li>\n		<li><em>New Catholic Encyclopedia</em>, 1st and 2nd eds, 1967 and 2003 [Ref BX841 .N44;&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/databases-by-title-a-z" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">online</a>, see under G for Gale Virtual Reference Library)]</li>\n		<li>{{dab},{125}, {Oxford Encyclopedia of the Reformation},{00}}<em>&nbsp;[Ref BR302.8 .O93 ]</em></li>\n		<li>&nbsp;{{dab},{182}, {Encyclopedia of Religion in America},{00}}[Ref. B2520 E52]</li>\n		<li><em>Encyclopedia of World Methodism</em>, 1974:&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofwo01harm" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">vol 1</a>&nbsp;(A-K) and<a class="external-link" href="http://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofwo02harm" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">vol 2</a>&nbsp;(L-Z)</li>\n		<li>{{dab},{238}, {Salem History Online},{00}}<em>&nbsp;</em></li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>Print&nbsp;\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li><em>New Westminster Dictionary of Church History</em>&nbsp;(Westminster, 2008) [Ref. BR95 .W496]</li>\n		<li><em>Encyclopedia of Early Christianity</em>&nbsp;(Garland, 1997) [Ref. BR162.2 .E5]</li>\n		<li><em>Dictionary of the Middle Ages</em>, 1982-1989 [Ref. D114 .O94 ]</li>\n		<li><em>Encyclopedia of Protestantism</em>, 2004 [Ref BX4811.3 .E53 ]</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Bibliography:&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166);">History Compass</a></p>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/databases-by-title-a-z" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Key periodical&nbsp;databases</a></p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>{{dab},{66}, {America History and Life},{00}}</li>\n	<li>{{dab},{74}, {Historical Abstracts},{00}}</li>\n	<li>{{dab},{90}, {International Medieval Bibliography Online},{00}}&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>{{dab},{58}, {Reader&#39;s Guide Retrospective},{00}}</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Newspaper databases (fulltext)</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>{{dab},{234}, {African American Newspapers: The 19th Century},{00}}</li>\n	<li>{America&#39;s Historical Newspapers},{00}}(example:&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://infoweb.newsbank.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/iw-search/we/HistArchive/?p_product=EANX&amp;p_theme=ahnp&amp;p_nbid=Q5CB52ILMTQwMjk0MDk0Ni44ODA0MjY6MToxMzoxOTIuMTA3LjM5LjE5&amp;p_action=doc&amp;s_lastnonissuequeryname=2&amp;d_viewref=search&amp;p_queryname=2&amp;p_docnum=2&amp;p_docref=v2:10D34C656629FD30@EANX-10FEF00D02BD6698@2363252-10FEF00D12AC5D70@0-10FEF00DEE44FC68@To%20the%20Printers%20of%20the%20Pennsylvania%20Gazette.%20Gentleman" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">obituary for Jonathan Edwards</a>)</li>\n	<li>{{dab},{159}, {New York Times Historical},{00}}</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Helpful websites</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/subject-databases" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Databases by Subjects</a>: scroll down to History&nbsp;</li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/resourcetype/historysites" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">History websites</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Literature</strong></p>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Literature in the curriculum: Novel Theologies (<a class="external-link" href="http://depts.drew.edu/regist/cl/ts10sp.html#*Basic%20Courses1*" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">TPHL310</a>)</p>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Key reference sources</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>{{dab},{42}, {Literature Criticism Online},{00}}</li>\n	<li>{{dab},{118}, {Contemporary Authors},{00}}</li>\n	<li>{{dab},{3}, {Literature Resource Center},{00}}</li>\n	<li>{{dab},{1094}, {Chambers Dictionary of Literary Characters},{00}}</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Key database: {{dab},{40}, {MLA Bibliography},{00}}&nbsp;(<a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/databases-by-title-a-z" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">see under M</a>)</p>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Helpful websites</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/subject-databases" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Databases by subjects</a>: scroll down to English</li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/resourcetype/englishsites" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Literature websites</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Interdisciplinary databases</strong></p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>&nbsp;{{dab},{4}, {Academic Search Premier},{00}}(see under A)</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;{{dab},{44}, {ProQuest Research Library},{00}}</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;{{dab},{91}, {JSTOR},{00}}</li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(270, 'Session 6: Social Science Resources for Theo ', '<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Psychology</strong></p>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Key reference sources</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li><em>Encyclopedia of Psychology</em>, 2000 [Ref. BF31 .E52]</li>\n	<li><em>Encyclopedia of Psychology and Religion</em>, 2010 (BL53 .E43)</li>\n	<li><em>Gale Encyclopedia of Mental Health</em>, 2008 [Ref.&nbsp;RC437 G36]</li>\n	<li><em>Mental Measurements Yearbooks</em>&nbsp;[Ref. BF431 .M46]<strong>&nbsp;</strong></li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://search.credoreference.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/content/entry/estpsyctheory/elsevier_s_dictionary_of_psychological_theories/0?searchId=8c276d4d-f58b-11e3-9a8a-0aea1e3b2a47&amp;result=0" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;"><em>Elsevier&#39;s Dictionary of Psychological Theories</em></a>, 2006.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Key database:&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/databases-by-title-a-z" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">PsycInfo&nbsp;</a>(search under &quot;P&quot;)</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>Note options to limit by Age Groups, Document Type, Methodology, etc.</li>\n	<li>Note that many&nbsp;of the articles accessed list all the additional articles they reference (e.g. &quot;<a class="external-link" href="http://web.a.ebscohost.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/ehost/detail?vid=3&amp;sid=4f1baa54-5773-4e64-b9b0-09c553333a3c%40sessionmgr4004&amp;hid=4214&amp;bdata=JnNpdGU9ZWhvc3QtbGl2ZSZzY29wZT1zaXRl#db=psyh&amp;AN=2014-02506-007" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Engaging in Grief Ministry</a>...&quot;&ndash;see Cited References)</li>\n	<li>Note Thesaurus</li>\n	<li>Note that dissertations are included (find the full text of them&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://search.proquest.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/pqdthss?accountid=10558" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">here</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Helpful websites</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>Databases by subject:&nbsp;Psychology (<a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/subject-databases" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">see under P</a>)&nbsp;</li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/resourcetype/psychologysites" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Another listing</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Sociology</strong></p>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Key reference sources&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li><em>New&nbsp;Blackwell Companion to the Sociology of Religion</em>, 2010 [Ref. BL60 .B53]</li>\n	<li><em>Blackwell Encyclopedia of Sociology,</em>&nbsp;2007 [Ref. HM425 .B53]</li>\n	<li><em>Encyclopedia of Religion and Society</em>, 1998 [Ref.BL60 .E53; and&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://hirr.hartsem.edu/ency/web.htm" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">online</a>]</li>\n	<li><em>Encyclopedia of&nbsp;Religion and Nature</em>, 2005 [Ref BL31 .E465; also&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://www.oxfordreference.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/views/BOOK_SEARCH.html?book=t304&amp;authstatuscode=200" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">online</a>]</li>\n	<li><em>Class in America</em>, 2007 [Ref. HN90 .S6 C564]</li>\n	<li><em>Encyclopedia of Social Work,</em>&nbsp;2008 [<a class="external-link" href="http://www.oxfordreference.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/view/10.1093/acref/9780195306613.001.0001/acref-9780195306613" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">online</a>]</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Key database:&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/databases-by-title-a-z" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">SocIndex</a>&nbsp;(Search under&nbsp;&quot;S&quot;)&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Helpful government websites</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.census.gov/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">U.S. Census Bureau&nbsp;</a>(for much statistically based information, e.g., on&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://www.census.gov/prod/2014pubs/p60-248.pdf" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Poverty</a>)&nbsp;</li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.bls.gov/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Bureau of Labor Statistics&nbsp;</a>(for reports based on labor statistics, e.g. &quot;<a class="external-link" href="http://www.bls.gov/cps/cpswp2012.pdf" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Profile of the Working Poor</a>&quot;)</li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.gpo.gov/fdsys/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">GPO Access&nbsp;</a>(for other government information, e.g. &quot;<a class="external-link" href="http://www.gpo.gov/fdsys/pkg/DCPD-201400409/pdf/DCPD-201400409.pdf" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">My Brother&#39;s Keeper</a>&quot;)</li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.state.gov/j/drl/irf/rpt/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">U.S. Dept. of State reports on religious freedom</a></li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.state.gov/j/drl/rls/hrrpt/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">U.S. Dept. of State human rights reports</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Other websites in sociology</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>Databases by subject:&nbsp;Sociology (<a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/subject-databases" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">see under S</a>)</li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/resourcetype/sociologysites" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Another listing</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><strong>Anthropology and Ethnic Studies&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Key reference sources</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://site.ebrary.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/lib/drew/docDetail.action?docID=10485575" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Multicultural America: An Encyclopedia of the Newest Americans</a>, 2011</li>\n	<li><em>Companion to Racial and Ethnic Studies</em>, 2002 [Ref. HT1521 .C65]</li>\n	<li><em>Encyclopedia of Race and Ethnic Studies</em>, 2004 (GN495.6 .C37)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Useful cross references in the Catalog: See Under</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>Ethnology</li>\n	<li>Ethnology United States (and other countries, e.g. Cameroon, Congo, etc)</li>\n	<li>Indians of North America&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Key databases</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>{{dab},{147}, {Anthropology Plus},{00}}(see under &quot;A&quot;)</li>\n	<li>{{dab},{71}, {Ethnic Newswatch},{00}}&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Helpful government websites&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://memory.loc.gov/frd/cs/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Library of Congress Country Studies</a></li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.state.gov/r/pa/ei/bgn/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">U. S. Dept. of State Background Notes</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Other websites in Anthropology and Ethnic Studies</p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>Databases by subject: Anthropology (<a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/subject-databases" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">see under A</a>)</li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/resourcetype/anthropologysites" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Another listing</a></li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL);
