(277, 'Current News', 'There are multiple places to find information on current events. &nbsp;Twitter feeds, blogs, and newspapers can all be helpful. &nbsp;If you&#39;re looking for articles from newspapers, past articles (1 day old or more) can be found in ProQuest Research Library or ProQuest Newsstand. &nbsp;For less formal (and less vetted) sources, try Twitter or various websites. &nbsp;You can locate blog postings by Googling with relevant terms (ex: &nbsp;&quot;michael brown&quot; ferguson blog).<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{160}, {Proquest Newsstand},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/Newsstand.jpg" style="width: 550px; height: 321px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;" /><br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{44}, {ProQuest Research Library},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1095}, {Twitter Search},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1096}, {Huffington Post},{00}}<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
