(320, 'Citation help', '<strong style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Electronic citation managment</strong><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">{{dab},{1045}, {EndnoteWeb},{11}}</span><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">(Beware: No citation software is perfect--check your work!) &nbsp;</span><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Endnote+Web+Bibliographic+Software" style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" target="_blank">Instructions for EndNote Web</a><br />\n<br />\n<strong style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Drew University&#39;s plagiarism policy</strong><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Take time to familiarize yourself with Drew&#39;s policy on plagiarism. &nbsp;<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Handbook/Academic+Integrity+policy" target="_blank">CLICK HERE</a>&nbsp;for a link to&nbsp;the &quot;Academic Integrity&quot; section of Drew&#39;s Student Handbook which&nbsp;contains a&nbsp;description of the plagiarism policy.</span><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<br />\n<strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">Reference Books (Located on C Level of library)</span></strong><br style="font-size: 13px;" />\n<span style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">Lipson, Charles.&nbsp;</span><i style="zoom: 1; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">Doing Honest Work in College: How to Prepare Citations, Avoid Plagiarism, and Achieve Real Academic Success</i><span style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">. Chicago: University of Chicago Press, 2004. Print .</span><span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: -webkit-center; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">PN171 .F56 L56 2004</span><br />\n<br />\n<strong>Citation Help<br />\n<br />\nAmerican Institute of Physics publishing guidelines, including citation guidance</strong><br />\nA &quot;how to&quot; prepare a scientific paper for publishing to conform to AIP requirements {{fil},{_mashmun/AIP_publishing_guidelines.pdf}, {AIP_publishing_guidelines.pdf}}<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Web resources for citation help in other styles</strong><br />\n{{dab},{316}, {MLA Formatting and Style Guide &ndash; The OWL at Purdue},{11}}<br />\n<br />\n<strong style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Reference Books shelved near Research Help Desk.</strong><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Gibaldi, Joseph.&nbsp;MLA Style Manual and Guide to Scholarly Publishing. New York: Modern Language Association of America, 2008. Print. Reference Counter PN147 .G444 2008</span><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<br />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Gibaldi, Joseph, and Modern Language Association of America.&nbsp;MLA Handbook for Writers of Research Papers. New York: Modern Language Association of America, 2009. Print. Reference Counter LB2369 .G53 2009</span><br />\n<br />\nLipson, Charles.&nbsp;Cite Right : A Quick Guide to Citation Styles--Mla, Apa, Chicago, the Sciences, Professions, and More. 2006.&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Reference Counter &nbsp;PN171 .F56 L55 2006</span><br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
