(322, 'Organizing thought', 'These tools will help you find basic information on thinkers, concepts, and literature, help organize and explain ancient perceptions, and trace the development of modern philosophies and schools of thought from Classical roots.<br />\n<br />\n<em>Oxford Classical Dictionary</em> is available online and also in book form in our Reference collection.<br />\n<br />\n<em>Dictionary of the History of Ideas</em><br />\n<br />\n<em>Classical Thought</em><br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(323, 'Full text information', 'Our JSTOR database is an excellent and easy to use resource for research in Classical Studies in general or in particular areas such as Philosophy, History, Archaeology, Literature, and Art. &nbsp;Look up ancient thinkers, connect them with modern philosphers, find information on particular concepts, and so on. &nbsp;All is full text!<br />\nStart from the Library Research Resources page: &nbsp;www.drew.edu/library/research<br />\nUse the &quot;List of resources by title (A-Z)&quot; and click JSTOR on the J page.<br />\nClick on &quot;Advanced Search&quot; at top of JSTOR page.&nbsp; Searching is by key word on two or more lines.<br />\nAristotle<br />\nAnd<br />\nVirtue or Character', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
