and Social Revolution in Bohemia</a>, by Thomas Fudge, 2010</li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://site.ebrary.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/lib/drew/docDetail.action?docID=10313705" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">*Women and the Reformation</a><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">, by Stjerna, 2009</span></li>\n	<li><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">*</span><a class="external-link" href="http://site.ebrary.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/lib/drew/docDetail.action?docID=10054639" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">The Catholic Reformation</a><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">, by Michael Mullett, 1999</span></li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://site.ebrary.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/lib/drew/docDetail.action?docID=10234745" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">*Companion to Anabaptism and Spiritualism, 1521-1700</a><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">. ed. by J Roth &amp; J Stayer, 2007</span></li>\n	<li>For more ebooks, search&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://site.ebrary.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/lib/drew/home.action" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Ebrary</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://www.oxfordscholarship.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/browse?t1=religion" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Oxford Scholarship Online</a></li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(345, 'Primary Sources & Websites', '<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li><a href="http://www.churchhistory.org/">American Society for Church History</a></li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.ccel.org/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;" target="_blank">Christian Classics Ethereal Library</a></li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.earlychristianwritings.com/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Early Christian Writings</a></li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://patristics.org/resources/encyclopedias/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">North American Patristics Society: Resources</a></li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.fourthcentury.com/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Fourth Century Christianity</a></li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://gnosis.org/welcome.html" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">The Gnosis Archive</a></li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.roger-pearse.com/weblog/patrologia-latina-pl-volumes-available-online/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Patrologia Latina</a></li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://www.medievalacademy.org/?page=Resources" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Medieval Academy of America: Resources</a></li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://medievalsourcesbibliography.org/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166);">Online Medieval Sources</a></li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://inpress.lib.uiowa.edu/feminae/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Feminae: Medieval Women and Gender Index</a></li>\n	<li><a href="http://wmich.edu/medieval/research/rawl/