(346, 'Periodical databases', '<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>{{dab},{85}, {ATLA Religion Database},{00}}&nbsp;</li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://web.ebscohost.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/ehost/search/advanced?sid=748b8424-c014-4033-b0f3-86c865c59bf9%40sessionmgr4&amp;vid=1&amp;hid=25" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">L&#39;Annee Philologique&nbsp;</a>&nbsp;</li>\n	<li><a class="external-link" href="http://apps.brepolis.net.ezproxy.drew.edu/bmb/search.cfm" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">International Medieval Bibliography</a>&nbsp;</li>\n	<li><a href="http://web.b.ebscohost.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/ehost/search/advanced?sid=13c28d6e-753b-412b-9ff1-8f62fcfd9d2c%40sessionmgr113&amp;vid=0&amp;hid=118">Historical Abstracts</a></li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(347, 'Other Resources', '<ul>\n	<li>{{dab},{16}, {Drew Library Catalog},{00}}</li>\n	<li>{{dab},{2}, {SUMMON},{00}}</li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(348, 'Journal Articles from a Citation', 'When you have a citation for a specific article, first identify the title of the&nbsp;<strong>journal</strong> (not the title of the article). &nbsp;Then go to Research Resources, and click on Journal List Search:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/Journal_list.jpg" style="width: 413px; height: 279px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;" /><br />\nNext, enter the journal title. &nbsp;If we have access to the journal for the year you need, click on the source, and then select the year/volume you need.<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(349, 'Table of Contents', '', NULL, 0, 'TOC', '{"ticked":"337,338,341,348,3,6,7"}', 0, 0, NULL),
(350, 'Background', 'Specialized encyclopedias and dictionaries give introductions to a topic or define specific vocabulary. &nbsp;Some useful titles include:<br />\n<br />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">{{dab},{1112}, {Concise Encyclopedia of Sociolinguistics, 2001.},{01}}</span><br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{51}, {Credo Reference},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1113}, {Dictionary of sociolinguistics, 2004.},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1082}, {Encyclopedia of Literary and Cultural Theory, 2011.},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1114}, {International Encyclopedia of Linguistics, 2003.},{01}}<br />\n{{dab},{1115}, {Key Ideas in Linguistics and the Philosophy of Language, 2012},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1116}, {Key Thinkers in Linguistics and the Philosophy of Language, 2005.},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1117}, {Routledge Encyclopedia of Linguistics, 2010.},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(351, 'Articles', '{{dab},{41}, {Linguistics &amp; Language Behavior Abstracts (LLBA)},{00}}<br />\nThe&nbsp;<strong>core</strong> database in the area. &nbsp;Start with keywrod searching, and use&nbsp;<em>subject</em> in the right-hand column to discover the specific term used within the database.<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/LLBA.jpg" style="width: 772px; height: 532px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;" /><br />\n<strong>Caution:</strong> &nbsp;Simply clicking on the subject term in the right column will search ONLY within the results of the keywrod search - in this case, retrieving 32 items. &nbsp;To expand your search, copy and paste the term in the search box.<br />\nIf you&#39;re working on a specific language, enter it as a&nbsp;<strong>subject</strong>.<br />\n<br />\nOther databases:<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{147}, {Anthropology Plus},{00}}<br />\nIndexes journal articles and essays in books on anthropology. &nbsp;You can often start by searching for&nbsp;<em>language OR linguist*</em> in Subject.<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{40}, {MLA Bibliography},{00}}<br />\nPrimarily indexes literary and film criticism, but also includes some material on linguistics.<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{53}, {SOCIndex},{00}}<br />\nIndexes the scholarly literature in sociology, which includes some coverage of sociolinguistics.<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{18}, {Google Scholar},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{2}, {SUMMON},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{159}, {New York Times Historical},{01}}', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(352, 'Books', 'Start with the <a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/catalog">Drew Library Catalog</a>, and begin with a keyword search in &quot;simple search&quot;: &nbsp;searching for&nbsp;<strong>code mixing</strong> retrieves this entry, and checking the Subject Termm identifies the exact heading you should search:<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/catalog.png" style="width: 660px; height: 331px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;" /><br />\n<br />\nThe Drew Library Catalog can be difficult to search effectively. &nbsp;You can also try <a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/er/worldcat">WorldCat</a>, the combined catalog of 10,000 libraries. &nbsp;If Drew does not own the material you need, click on &quot;Request an Inter-Library Loan&quot; and we&#39;ll get it for you from another library.', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(353, 'Full Text', '<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Click directly to the full text if available, or, if you are in a Drew database, click on <img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/AL.png" style="width: 81px; height: 21px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;to find the full text in another database. &nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nIf Drew does not own or have access to the material you want, request the material through <a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/interlibrary-loan-request">Interlibrary Loan</a>, and we&#39;ll get it for you from another library.</span>', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(354, 'Table of Contents', '', NULL, 0, 'TOC', '{"ticked":"350,351,353,352,3,6,7"}', 0, 0, NULL),
(355, 'Citation help', '<strong style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Electronic citation managment</strong><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">{{dab},{1045}, {EndnoteWeb},{11}}</span><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">(Beware: No citation software is perfect--check your work!) &nbsp;</span><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Endnote+Web+Bibliographic+Software" style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" target="_blank">Instructions for EndNote Web</a><br />\n<br />\n<strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">Reference Books</span></strong><br />\n<span style="font-size: 13px;">(Located on C Level of library)</span>\n<ul>\n	<li><span style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">Lipson, Charles.&nbsp;</span><i style="zoom: 1; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">Doing Honest Work in College: How to Prepare Citations, Avoid Plagiarism, and Achieve Real Academic Success</i><span style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">. Chicago: University of Chicago Press, 2004. Print .</span><span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: -webkit-center; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">PN171 .F56 L56 2004</span></li>\n</ul>\n(Shelved near Research Help Desk.)\n\n<ul>\n	<li>{{dab},{1121}, {ACS Style Guide},{11}}</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Web resources for citation help</strong><br />\n<strong>+ </strong>ACS Style Guides\n\n<ul>\n	<li>for Biochemistry&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\nClick <a href="http://pubs.acs.org.ezproxy.drew.edu/page/bichaw/submission/reference-guidelines.html">HERE</a> for ACS Publications&#39; guidelines for<strong> Biochemistry</strong><br />\n<br />\nACS Style Guide Excerpt<br />\nChap 14: References &nbsp;{{fil},{_mashmun/style_guide_2006.pdf}, {style_guide_2006.pdf}}\n<ul>\n	<li>{{dab},{1122}, {CAS Source Index (CASSI) Search Tool},{11}}</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<strong style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Drew University&#39;s plagiarism policy</strong><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Take time to familiarize yourself with Drew&#39;s policy on plagiarism. &nbsp;<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Handbook/Academic+Integrity+policy" target="_blank">CLICK HERE</a>&nbsp;for a link to&nbsp;the &quot;Academic Integrity&quot; section of Drew&#39;s Student Handbook which&nbsp;contains a&nbsp;description of the plagiarism policy.</span><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(356, 'Get full text', '<strong>Full text available&nbsp;</strong><br />\nClick directly to the full text if available in a database, or click on &nbsp; <img src="http://depts.drew.edu/lib/AL_button.gif" />&nbsp; &nbsp;to find the full text in another database.The&nbsp;<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Drew+ArticleLinker" target="_blank">Article Linker guide</a>&nbsp;provides additional instructions for finding full text, either online or in print/microfilm format within the library.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Full text not available</strong><br />\nDon&#39;t give up! &nbsp;There are other ways to get the information you are seeking.&nbsp;<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_mashmun/find_full_t.png" style="width: 468px; height: 582px;" /><br />\n{{dab},{1123}, {InterLibrary Loan},{11}}', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(358, 'Citing Your Sources', 'Be certain to use the format recommended by your professor.<br />\n<br />\n<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Endnote+Web+Bibliographic+Software">Endnote</a> will help you format your references (either parenthetical or endnotes), keep track of your articles, and set up your bibliography/reference list. &nbsp;Ask about it at the Research Helpdesk!', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(359, 'Table of Contents', '', NULL, 0, 'TOC', '{"ticked":"281,277,278,358,3,6,7"}', 0, 0, NULL),
(360, 'Search Summon', 'Summon is a google-like search of Drew Library Resources. You can look for books that are in the Drew Library with Summon, &nbsp;as well &nbsp;as academic (peer-reviewed or scholarly) &nbsp;articles, newspapers and &nbsp;other resources, such as vetted public websites.<br />\n<br />\nSummon can be found on the Research Resources page. &nbsp;<span style="font-size: 12.7272720336914px; line-height: 20.8000011444092px;">From&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.drew.edu/home/" style="font-size: 12.7272720336914px; line-height: 20.8000011444092px;" target="_blank">Treehouse</a><span style="font-size: 12.7272720336914px; line-height: 20.8000011444092px;">, click on Research Resources:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/research_resources.png" style="width: 372px; height: 122px;" /><br />\nType in keyword or phrase:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/summon_health_inequality.png" style="width: 517px; height: 93px;" /><br />\nAfter searching, you will get lots of options to narrow &nbsp;your search. Some key limits are:</span>\n<div>\n<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="filters" style="zoom: 1; margin-bottom: 0.7692em; color: rgb(77, 77, 77); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal; background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230);">\n	<tbody class="static" style="zoom: 1;">\n		<tr style="zoom: 1;">\n			<td class="facetLabel" style="zoom: 1; vertical-align: top; padding-top: 2px;"><label for="facet:is_peer_reviewed" style="zoom: 1;"><span class="label" style="zoom: 1; font-size: 12px;">Limit to articles from peer-reviewed publications</span></label><br />\n			<span style="color: rgb(77, 77, 77); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230);">Book / eBook<br />\n			Newspaper Article</span>\n			<div>&nbsp;</div>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/summon_filters.png" style="width: 214px; height: 543px;" /><br />\nThe more....button provides subtopics for your major topic. It&#39;s a very useful option because it helps to narrow your focus,</div>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(361, 'Find articles/newspapers/magazines', '<strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">From&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.drew.edu/home/" style="font-size: 13px;" target="_blank">Treehouse</a></strong><span style="font-size: 13px;"><strong>, click on Research Resources:</strong><br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/treehouse_research_resources.png" style="width: 363px; height: 127px;" /><br />\nClick on List of Resources by Title (A-Z)<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/a-z_list.png" style="width: 496px; height: 154px;" /></span><br style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px;">Academic Search Premier is a good place to start your search:</span><br style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px;" />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/academic_search_premier.png" style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px; width: 599px; height: 469px;" /><br style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px;" />\n<br />\n<span style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px;">These databases contain newspaper/popular magazine/scholarly articles</span>\n<ul style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px; margin: 0px;">\n	<li>Academic Search Premier</li>\n	<li>SocINDEX</li>\n	<li>ProQuest Political Science</li>\n	<li>ProQuest Research Library</li>\n	<li>LexisNexis - primarly newspapers:&nbsp;local, regional, national and international newspapers.</li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(362, 'Find full text', '<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Click directly to the full text if available (as pdf or html) or click on&nbsp;<img class="confluence-embedded-image confluence-external-resource" data-image-="" src="http://depts.drew.edu/lib/AL_button.gif" style="cursor: pointer; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; max-width: 100%;" />&nbsp;to find the full text in another database.The&nbsp;<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Drew+ArticleLinker" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Article Linker guide</a>provides additional instructions for finding full text, either online or in print/microfilm format within the library.</p>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">If the&nbsp;&nbsp;<img class="confluence-embedded-image confluence-external-resource confluence-content-image-border" data-image-="" src="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/download/attachments/32123158/AL_button.gif?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1377096646482&amp;api=v2" style="cursor: pointer; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 1px solid black; max-width: 100%;" />&nbsp;button doesn&#39;t provide access to the full text, you can request the article via<a href="https://illiad.drew.edu/illiad/Logon.html" target="_blank">&nbsp;InterLibraryLoan</a>.<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/request_an_ILL.png" style="width: 364px; height: 124px;" /><br />\n<br />\nThe first time you request an article or book via InterLibraryLoan, you &nbsp;will &nbsp;be asked to fill out a short form.&nbsp;<b>It may take several days to receive an article via InterLibraryLoan; &nbsp;books can take longer.</b></p>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(363, 'Search across Drew Library resources', '<span style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px;"><strong><a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research" target="_blank">Summon</a> is a google-like search of Drew Library Resources</strong>. You can look for books that are in the Drew Library with Summon, &nbsp;as well &nbsp;as academic (peer-reviewed or scholarly) &nbsp;articles, newspapers and &nbsp;other resources, such as vetted public websites.</span><br style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px;" />\n<br style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px;">Summon can be found on the Research Resources page. &nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12.7272720336914px; line-height: 20.8000011444092px;">From&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.drew.edu/home/" style="font-size: 12.7272720336914px; line-height: 20.8000011444092px;" target="_blank">Treehouse</a><span style="font-size: 12.7272720336914px; line-height: 20.8000011444092px;">, click on Research Resources:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/research_resources.png" style="width: 372px; height: 122px;" /><br />\nType in keyword or phrase:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/summon_crime_scene.png" style="width: 509px; height: 96px;" /><br />\nAfter searching, you will get lots of options to narrow &nbsp;your search. Some key limits are:</span>\n<div style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px;">\n<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="filters" style="zoom: 1; margin-bottom: 0.7692em; color: rgb(77, 77, 77); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: normal; background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230);">\n	<tbody class="static" style="zoom: 1;">\n		<tr style="zoom: 1;">\n			<td class="facetLabel" style="zoom: 1; vertical-align: top; padding-top: 2px;"><label for="facet:is_peer_reviewed" style="zoom: 1;"><span class="label" style="zoom: 1; font-size: 12px;">Limit to articles from peer-reviewed publications</span></label><br />\n			<span style="font-size: 12px;">Book / eBook</span>\n			<div>&nbsp;</div>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/summon_filters.png" style="width: 214px; height: 543px;" /><br />\nThe more....button provides subtopics for your major topic. It&#39;s a very useful option because it helps to narrow your focus,</div>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(364, 'Limit to scholarly/academic articles', '<strong><span style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px;">After searching, make &nbsp;sure to limit your search to Scholarly (Peer Reviewed) Journals</span></strong><br style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px;" />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/scholarly_articles.png" style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px; width: 257px; height: 284px;" />', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(365, 'Business/employment/demographic statistics', '<ul>\n	<li><strong>North American Industry Classification (NAICS)</strong> codes<a href="http://www.census.gov/eos/www/naics/" target="_blank">&nbsp;http://www.census.gov/eos/www/naics/</a></li>\n	<li>The<strong> Bureau of Labor Statistics</strong> provides employment statistics by industry, and by NAICS code (denotes specific jobs/occupations) :<a href="http://www.bls.gov/" target="_blank">​http://www.bls.gov/</a></li>\n	<li><strong>U.S. Small Business Administration</strong>:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sba.gov/" target="_blank">http://www.sba.gov/</a></li>\n	<li><strong>Economic Census </strong>data:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.census.gov/econ/census/" target="_blank">http://www.census.gov/econ/census/</a></li>\n	<li>Find <strong>community facts</strong> (what are the demographics for where you want to establish your business)<a href="http://factfinder2.census.gov/faces/nav/jsf/pages/index.xhtml" target="_blank">&nbsp;http://factfinder2.census.gov/faces/nav/jsf/pages/index.xhtml</a></li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(366, 'Information about companies and industries', '<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Linked from:</span><a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/databases-by-title-a-z" style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" target="_blank">&nbsp;List of Resources by Title</a>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Business Source Elite</strong> has a &quot;Company Profiles&quot; option: MarketLine reports.</li>\n	<li><strong>LexisNexis</strong> provides Hoover reports for companies. LexisNexis also provides access to national and international news stories, including business news. You can also find industry overviews here. You will need to know the SIC code that your product/service falls under. Look up SIC codes at:<strong>&nbsp;<a href="http://siccode.com/en" target="_blank">http://siccode.com/en</a>&nbsp;.</strong> The&nbsp;North American Industry Classification (NAICS) codes<a href="http://www.census.gov/eos/www/naics/" target="_blank">&nbsp;http://www.census.gov/eos/www/naics/</a>&nbsp;can also be helpful in searching for industry/company information about your product/service.</li>\n	<li><strong>ABI-Inform</strong> has trade/professional business new stories and company reports and news.</li>\n	<li><strong>SEC </strong>reports (Secruties and Exchange Commission), annual reports required by law of publically owned companies&nbsp;<a href="http://www.sec.gov/edgar/searchedgar/companysearch.html" target="_blank">&nbsp;http://www.sec.gov/edgar/searchedgar/companysearch.html</a></li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(367, 'Databases', 'Linked from:<a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/databases-by-title-a-z" target="_blank"> List of Resources by Title</a><br />\n<br />\n<strong>Find scholarly, peer reviewed academic articles on your business topic:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Business Source Elite</li>\n	<li>ABI Inform</li>\n	<li>Academic Search Premier</li>\n	<li>EconLit - Economic theory rather than strictly business.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong><span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Find newspaper articles/company info/industry info/legal issues/regulations:</span></strong>\n\n<ul style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">\n	<li>LexisNexis Academic contains hundreds of local, national and international newspapers and other news sources. From the default search page, click on &quot;Search by content source&quot;&nbsp;The following screen lets you pick news, company/industry&nbsp;information&nbsp;or legal resources&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/lexis_nexis_default.png" style="opacity: 0.9; line-height: 20.7999992370605px; width: 679px; height: 157px;" /><br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/lexis_nexis_by_type.png" style="opacity: 0.9; line-height: 20.7999992370605px; width: 571px; height: 442px;" /><br />\n<strong><span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">What area(s) does my business cover?&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></strong>\n\n<ul style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">\n	<li>Find &nbsp;relevant databases by using the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/subject-databases" target="_blank">List of Resources by Subject</a>&nbsp;option.</li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(368, 'Table of Contents', '', NULL, 0, 'TOC', '{"ticked":"374,317,318,319,320,321,3,7,6,316"}', 0, 0, NULL),
(369, 'What is a scholarly article?', '<strong>Let&#39;s compare a popular and scholarly article:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Popular</strong> =&nbsp;<a href="http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&amp;db=pwh&amp;AN=16762397&amp;site=pov-live" target="_blank">http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&amp;db=pwh&amp;AN=16762397&amp;site=pov-live</a></li>\n	<li><strong>Scholarly</strong> =&nbsp;{{fil},{_epatters/crimeshowviewinghabits.pdf}, {crimeshowviewinghabits.pdf}}</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<strong>Identifying a scholarly journals/articles:</strong>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Identifying+Scholarly+Journals" target="_blank">https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Identifying+Scholarly+Journals</a></li>\n	<li>{{dab},{1120}, {Strategies for reading journal articles. },{01}}</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<strong>Reading scholarly articles:&nbsp;</strong>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style="font-size: 12.727272033691406px;">{{dab},{1119}, {Examples of critical reading.},{01}}</span></li>\n	<li>{{dab},{1118}, {Strategies for reading journal articles - checklist},{01}}</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(370, 'InterLibrary Loan', 'InterLibrary Loan is a terrific service offered by the Drew Library. If the Drew Library doesn&#39;t &nbsp;own or provide access to a resource you need, you can order that resource through InterLibrary Loan. Read about how to get an ILL account and how to request books/articles:<br />\n<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Interlibrary+Loan+Policies" target="_blank">https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Interlibrary+Loan+Policies</a>', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(371, 'Search Tips', 'Place quotation marks around phrases.<br />\n<strong>&quot;crime scene&quot;</strong><br />\nUse an asterix to truncate or finish of the ends of words.<br />\n<b>verdict* = verdict/verdicts</b><br />\nCapitalize AND to connect concepts.<br />\n<strong>&quot;crime scene&quot; AND verdict*</strong><br />\nCapitalize OR to search for synonyms.<br />\n<strong>verdict* OR juries</strong><br />\nUse parenthese to &quot;nest&quot; a search.<br />\n<strong>&quot;crime scene&quot; AND (verdict* OR juries)</strong><br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(372, 'Background ', 'Sometimes a topic is mentioned in class, or a word is used in reading, that leads to other questions. &nbsp;In those cases, a quick look at a dictionary or encyclopedia might be useful. &nbsp;Some potential sources:<br />\n<br />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">{{dab},{1126}, {Handbook of Forensic Anthropology and Archaeology, 2009},{01}}</span><br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1127}, {Forensic Science: An Encyclopedia of History, Methods and Techniques},{00}}', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(374, 'Library Activity', '<strong>Library Hunt</strong><br />\nAs part of your visit to the Library, you will have an opportunity to get accustomed to using our resources by completing the activity as descibed in the &quot;Library Hunt&quot; Google Form below.<br />\n<br />\nLink to &quot;Library Hunt&quot; Google Form<br />\n<a href="https://docs.google.com/a/drew.edu/forms/d/1cvnBU-FE6crvXtLuRTHBoROkQyNaJUdS60xk6FM2HUQ/viewform">https://docs.google.com/a/drew.edu/forms/d/1cvnBU-FE6crvXtLuRTHBoROkQyNaJUdS60xk6FM2HUQ/viewform</a>', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(376, 'Formatting Bibliographies', 'Use <a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Endnote+Web+Bibliographic+Software">EndNote Web</a> to help with formatting your references and bibliographies. &nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(377, 'Table of Contents', '', NULL, 0, 'TOC', '{"ticked":"372,242,241,243,245,244,246,261,262,3,6,7,376"}', 0, 0, NULL),
(378, 'Library Activitiy', '<strong>Library Hunt</strong><br />\nAs part of your visit to the Library, you will have an opportunity to get accustomed to using our resources by completing the activity as described in the &quot;Library Hunt&quot; Google Form linked below (you must be logged into Drew account to access).<br />\n<br />\n<a href="https://docs.google.com/a/drew.edu/forms/d/1TgDdVsn5NHTeVyt1ksZtzWJDz8BQo3Yv4SgTMSEHkBc/viewform">https://docs.google.com/a/drew.edu/forms/d/1TgDdVsn5NHTeVyt1ksZtzWJDz8BQo3Yv4SgTMSEHkBc/viewform</a><br />\n<br />\nComplete the activity and log your answers into the paper or electronic form provided.&nbsp;<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(379, 'Identifying scholarly and popular articles ', 'When seeking sources, you will need to be able to determine whether or not an item is scholarly. Links below to for help.<br />\n<br />\n<a href="http://www.lib.ncsu.edu/tutorials/scholarly-popular/">Scholary and Popular Materials (LINK).</a>&nbsp; Excellent explanation of how to identify different sources with good graphics.&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">From NC State University Libary.</span><br />\n<br />\n<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Identifying+Scholarly+Journals">Identifying Scholarly Journals (LINK)&nbsp;</a>&nbsp;Detailed guidelines for identifying scholarly and popular journals. From Drew University Library.', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(381, 'Table of Contents', '', NULL, 0, 'TOC', '{"ticked":"383,416,382,384,385,3,7,6"}', 0, 0, NULL),
(382, 'Get full text', '<strong>Full text available&nbsp;</strong><br />\nClick directly to the full text if available in a database, or click on &nbsp; <img src="http://depts.drew.edu/lib/AL_button.gif" />&nbsp; &nbsp;to find the full text in another database.The&nbsp;<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Drew+ArticleLinker" target="_blank">Article Linker guide</a>&nbsp;provides additional instructions for finding full text, either online or in print/microfilm format within the library.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Full text not available</strong><br />\nDon&#39;t give up! &nbsp;There are other ways to get the information you are seeking.&nbsp;<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_mashmun/find_full_t.png" style="width: 468px; height: 582px;" /><br />\n{{dab},{1123}, {InterLibrary Loan},{11}}', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(383, 'Databases', '<ul>\n	<li>{{dab},{4}, {Academic Search Premier},{11}}</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul>\n	<li>{{dab},{217}, {American Chemical Society Journals},{11}}</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">&nbsp;{{dab},{18}, {Google Scholar},{11}}<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">​</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul>\n	<li>{{dab},{206}, {Proquest Science Journals},{11}} <span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;"><span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">​</span>&nbsp;</span></li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul>\n	<li>{{dab},{23}, {PubMed},{11}}</li>\n</ul>\nMany&nbsp;ways to limit searches (age group, gender, language, type of study).<br />\n<br />\n&gt; Related documents are determined by number of repetitions of search words.<br />\n&gt; Offers some free content.&nbsp; Check to see if other articles of interest are available in full text through the Drew Library.<br />\n&gt; Find the PMID on the record and copy that number into the appropriate box on the Electronic Journals search page.<br />\n&gt; For more detailed instructions with screen shots, see:&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/x/SYFUAQ" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/x/SYFUAQ</a><br />\nSearch help:\n<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n	<li>PubMed Basics&nbsp;<a class="external-link" data-mce-="" href="http://nnlm.gov/training/resources/pmtri.pdf" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">http://nnlm.gov/training/resources/pmtri.pdf</a><a href="http://nnlm.gov/training/resources/pmtri.pdf" target="_blank">&nbsp;</a></li>\n	<li>Searching with MeSH (<strong>Me</strong>dical&nbsp;<strong>S</strong>ubject&nbsp;<strong>H</strong>eadings)&nbsp;<a class="external-link" data-mce-="" href="http://nnlm.gov/training/resources/meshtri.pdf" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">http://nnlm.gov/training/resources/meshtri.pdf</a><a href="http://nnlm.gov/training/resources/meshtri.pdf" target="_blank">&nbsp;</a></li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">{{dab},{29}, {ScienceDirect},{11}}</span></li>\n</ul>\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">​</span><span style="font-size: 13px; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">Students have access to a core group of journals to which Drew University subscribes. For unsubscribed content, students will&nbsp;use the Interlibrary Loan system (</span><a href="http://illiad.drew.edu/" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204); font-size: 13px; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;" target="_blank">illiad.drew.edu</a><span style="font-size: 13px; font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">) to request articles outside our subscriptions; Interlibrary Loan will then download and supply the articles through ILLiad.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">To do this easily:</span>\n\n<ul style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">\n	<li>Click on the &quot;Search For Article&quot; button on the article in ScienceDirect&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Then, click &ldquo;Request through InterLibrary Loan&rdquo; on the bottom of the following screen.</li>\n	<li>Sign into your ILLiad &nbsp;account and the article information will automatically fill in the appropriate spots in the form.</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;Type &#39;0&#39; in the spot marked &ldquo;Max you are willing to pay&rdquo;</li>\n	<li>Click &ldquo;Submit request&rdquo;.</li>\n</ul>\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">You should receive the article in 24 - 72 hours.</span><br />\n<br />\nTIPS: Limit to&nbsp;Journals. In the dropdown to the right of your search term,&nbsp;focus your search by limiting to Title, Abstract, Keyword.<br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<img src="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/download/attachments/36668100/image2014-2-14%2016%3A9%3A17.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1392412157853&amp;api=v2" style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" /><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n{{dab},{91}, {JSTOR},{11}}\n<ul>\n	<li>Medicine and allied health</li>\n	<li>Sciences and mathematics</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{215}, {SciFinder},{11}}<br />\n<strong>First time users of SciFinder need to register for an account. Use a Drew networked computer and follow the&nbsp;<a data-mce-="" href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/x/Z5FjAQ" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">directions for registering</a><a href="http://up.https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/download/attachments/23302503/SciFinder-User-Registration.pdf?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1376920327430" target="_blank">.</a></strong><br />\n&nbsp;\n<ul>\n	<li>Indexes all of&nbsp;<em>Chemical Abstracts</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>Medline.</em>&nbsp;(Duplicate Medline references are removed by default.)</li>\n	<li>Search using natural language, molecular formula, or substance. Searches can be refined.</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Links to:</li>\n</ul>\n&gt; citing and cited articles (useful for finding related articles)<br />\n&gt; reactions<br />\n&gt; substances<br />\n&nbsp;\n<ul>\n	<li>Get full text links to our article linker to find electronic full text. If Drew doesn&#39;t have full text online, we might have the journal in print or microform.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul>\n	<li>To find out, take citation information and go to the&nbsp;<a class="external-link" data-mce-="" href="https://librarycat.drew.edu/" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166) !important; text-decoration: none;">Library Catalog</a>&gt; Browse&gt; [enter the title of the JOURNAL without abbreviations] and search by periodical title, looking at the holdings to see if the Library holds the date range you need in print or microform.</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n{{dab},{80}, {Web of Science and Knowledge (ISI Citation Indexes)},{11}}\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>Web of Science\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li>&gt;Topic searching searches title, abstract. To limit further, try limiting to title.</li>\n		<li>&gt; Within searches you can limit within topic (as decided by journal title), author, affiliation, year.</li>\n		<li>&gt; Can analyze results, get related (articles with citations in common with the source article).</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li>Biological Abstracts\n	<ul style="margin: 0px; list-style-type: disc;">\n		<li>&gt; Topic searching searches title, abstract. To limit further, try limiting to title.</li>\n		<li>&gt; Within searches you can limit within topic (as decided by journal title), author, subject area, concept code, super taxa.</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>&nbsp; NOTES:&nbsp;</em></p>\n\n<ul style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">\n	<li style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><em>If an item of interest appears in both Science Citation Index and Biological Abstracts, you can toggle back and forth between the two databases, giving you the advantage of both citation indexing and subject indexing.</em></li>\n	<li><em>Selecting<strong> All Databases</strong>&nbsp;searches Science Citation Index, Biological Abstracts and Medline. The result will indicate the database from which it was retrieved.</em></li>\n	<li><em>Citations can be saved directly to EndNote Web from these databases.</em></li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(384, 'Citation help', '<strong style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Electronic citation managment</strong><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">{{dab},{1045}, {EndnoteWeb},{11}}</span><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">(Beware: No citation software is perfect--check your work!) &nbsp;</span><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Endnote+Web+Bibliographic+Software" style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" target="_blank">Instructions for EndNote Web</a><br />\n<br />\n<strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">Reference books and resources</span></strong><br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1121}, {ACS Style Guide},{11}}<br />\n<br />\n<strong style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">ACS Style Guide Excerpt&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Chap 14: References &nbsp;{{fil},{_mashmun/style_guide_2006.pdf}, {style_guide_2006.pdf}}</span><br />\n<br />\nCouncil of Science Editors. Style Manual Committee.<strong>&nbsp;Scientific Style and Format: The CSE Manual for Authors, Editors, and Publishers.</strong> Reference Desk T11 .S386 2006<br />\n<br />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">Lipson, Charles.&nbsp;</span><i style="font-size: 13px; zoom: 1; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">Doing Honest Work in College: How to Prepare Citations, Avoid Plagiarism, and Achieve Real Academic Success</i><span style="font-size: 13px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">. Chicago: University of Chicago Press, 2004. Print .</span><span style="line-height: 20.7999992370605px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: -webkit-center;">PN171 .F56 L56 2004</span><br />\n<br />\n<strong>Web resources for citation help</strong><br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1122}, {CAS Source Index (CASSI) Search Tool},{11}}<br />\n<br />\n<strong style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Drew University&#39;s plagiarism policy</strong><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Take time to familiarize yourself with Drew&#39;s policy on plagiarism. &nbsp;<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Handbook/Academic+Integrity+policy" target="_blank">CLICK HERE</a>&nbsp;for a link to&nbsp;the &quot;Academic Integrity&quot; section of Drew&#39;s Student Handbook which&nbsp;contains a&nbsp;description of the plagiarism policy.</span><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL);
