(388, 'Journal Resources', '<h4 id="MATResourcesforTeachersofEnglish-EnglishJournal" style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><a class="external-link" href="http://pb7zv8tc5d.search.serialssolutions.com/log?L=PB7ZV8TC5D&amp;D=PRA&amp;J=ENGLJOU&amp;U=http%3A%2F%2Fezproxy.drew.edu%2Flogin%3Furl%3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Fproquest.umi.com%2Fpqdweb%3FRQT%3D318%26pmid%3D28857" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">English Journal</a></h4>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">From the National Council of Teachers of English: directed at High School Teachers. For Middle School/Junior High teachers, try&nbsp;<a class="external-link" href="http://pb7zv8tc5d.search.serialssolutions.com/log?L=PB7ZV8TC5D&amp;D=PRA&amp;J=VOICFROTHEMI&amp;U=http%3A%2F%2Fezproxy.drew.edu%2Flogin%3Furl%3Dhttp%3A%2F%2Fproquest.umi.com%2Fpqdweb%3FRQT%3D318%26pmid%3D34901" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">Voices from the Middle.</a></p>\n\n<h4 id="MATResourcesforTeachersofEnglish-CollegeEnglish" style="margin: 20px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><a class="external-link" href="http://proquest.umi.com.ezproxy.drew.edu/pqdweb?RQT=318&amp;pmid=28856" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">College English</a></h4>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Also from the National Council of Teachers of English.</p>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(389, 'Finding Books', '<h4 id="MATResourcesforTeachersofEnglish-DrewLibrarycatalog" style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">{{dab},{16}, {Drew Library Catalog},{00}}</h4>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Drew&#39;s book resources on social studies topics are many and varied. The online catalog allows you to search for books by keyword, or scan by exact subject heading. Our resources tend more toward literature than education, though, so try Worldcat for more information.</p>\n\n<h4 id="MATResourcesforTeachersofEnglish-Worldcat" style="margin: 20px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">{{dab},{94}, {Worldcat},{00}}</h4>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Looking for a specific book or wider coverage than Drew has? Use Worldcat to search across the catalogs of many libraries, then use &quot;Borrow this Item from another Library&quot; to request the book through our Interlibrary Loan service.<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{51}, {Credo Reference},{01}}</p>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(390, 'Literature-specific Resources', '<h4 id="MATResourcesforTeachersofEnglish-MLABibliography" style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">{{dab},{40}, {MLA Bibliography},{00}}</h4>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">The MLA-- Modern Language Association- Bibliography is the&nbsp;<em>grande dame</em>&nbsp;of literary and language research tools. This database is useful for finding literature criticism and some material on the teaching of English. Unfortunately, the MLA Bibliography doesn&#39;t include abstracts (short descriptions) of the content of the articles and books it points to, nor does it include full text, though full text available through other &#39;Ebsco&#39; databases may pop up. Watch out for Ph.D. dissertations.</p>\n\n<h4 id="MATResourcesforTeachersofEnglish-LiteratureResourceCenter" style="margin: 20px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">{{dab},{3}, {Literature Resource Center},{00}}</h4>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">This first-stop resource for literature includes Author biographies, work overviews, literary criticism and bibliographies. Best searched by author name or work title. Use the tabs at the top of your search results to see different types of articles. However, stay away from the &quot;Multimedia&quot; category-- it can turn up really random results.</p>\n\n<h4 id="MATResourcesforTeachersofEnglish-LiteratureCriticismOnline" style="margin: 20px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">{{dab},{42}, {Literature Criticism Online},{00}}</h4>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Online version of&nbsp;<em>Contemporary Literary Criticism</em>&nbsp;(CLC)<em>, Nineteenth-Century Literary Criticism</em>&nbsp;(NCLC)<em>, Drama Criticism</em>and&nbsp;<em>Twentieth-Century Literary Criticism</em>&nbsp;sets. Collects critical writing about literary works/authors.</p>\n\n<p style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><a class="external-link" href="http://www.drew.edu/library/resourcetype/englishsites" rel="nofollow" style="color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none;">More online resources for English</a></p>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
