(444, 'Databases', '<span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px;">From&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.drew.edu/home/" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">Treehouse</a><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px;">, click on Research Resources:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/treehouse_research_resources.png" style="width: 363px; height: 127px;" /></span><br />\n<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">Click on List of Resources by Title (A-Z)</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/a-z_list.png" style="width: 496px; height: 154px;" /><br />\n<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">Academic Search Premier is a good place to start your search:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/academic_search_premier.png" style="width: 599px; height: 469px;" /><br />\nUse separate search boxes for separate topics.</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">Use quotations marks &quot;&quot; for phrases: &quot;united states&quot;</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">Connect synonyms with OR: &quot;united states&quot; OR america*</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">Use the asterix * to truncate words:&nbsp;</span>\n<div style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; line-height: 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">america* = america/american<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/citizenship_academic_search_premier_001.png" style="width: 782px; height: 204px;" /><br />\n<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">After searching, make &nbsp;sure to limit your search to Scholarly (Peer Reviewed) Journals<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/scholarly_articles.png" style="width: 257px; height: 284px;" /></span><br />\n<br />\n<strong>Other good databases to search are:</strong></div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; line-height: 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">Worldwide Political Science&nbsp;</li>\n	<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; line-height: 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">Proquest Political Science</li>\n	<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; line-height: 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">Proquest Research Library</li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(445, 'Books', 'Find &nbsp;books in the<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">&nbsp;</span><a href="https://librarycat.drew.edu/web2/tramp2.exe/goto/A05uajqd.000?screen=searchsimple.html" style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" target="_blank">Drew Catalog</a> with a simple keyword search.<br />\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;OR<br />\nuse for the <strong>exact</strong> search option:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/exact_search.png" style="width: 345px; height: 370px;" /><br />\nUse the drop down menu to select <strong>subjects</strong>. Type in your subject: <strong>citizenship:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/catalog_exact_citizenship.png" style="width: 653px; height: 88px;" /></strong><br />\n<b>Citizenship results in 99 titles, with sub topics alphabetically listed below:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/catalog_exact_citizenship_results.png" style="width: 424px; height: 386px;" /><br />\nThis is a very focused way to search the Drew Library Catalog.</b><br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(446, 'Locating Books', 'Use &quot;Simple&quot; (rather than &quot;Exact&quot;) in the <a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/catalog">Drew Catalog</a>, and search the name of the author or director. &nbsp;This will pick up books with chapters or essays about your author/director, while using &quot;Exact&quot; will retrieve only those items that are all about the particular person.<br />\n<br />\nFor more resources, check <a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/er/worldcat">WorldCat</a>, the combined catalog of 10,000 libraries. &nbsp;If Drew does not own the items you identify, request them through Interlibrary Loan (embedded in WorldCat) - that will take 2 days to 2 weeks, so plan ahead!', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(447, 'Citing Sources', 'MLA (Modern Language Association) or Chicago styles are the most commonly accepted formats in the languages. &nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">A useful guide to MLA style is&nbsp;</span><a href="http://owl.english.purdue.edu/owl/resource/747/01/" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">MLA Formatting and Style Guide &ndash; The OWL at Purdue</a><font color="#000000" face="Verdana, Arial, sans-serif"><span style="line-height: 19.5px;">. &nbsp;OWL also has a guide to <a href="https://owl.english.purdue.edu/owl/resource/717/01/">Chicago style</a>. &nbsp;Paper copies of both manuals are available at the Research Helpdesk in the Library.</span></font><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<a href="http://www.myendnoteweb.com/" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">EndnoteWeb</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">&nbsp;</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">Free software to help manage your bibliographic needs, inlcuding organizing sources and citations by project, &nbsp;sharing citations for group work, and for &quot;citing while you write&quot;, i.e. inserting citations into papers while writing. &nbsp;</span>', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(448, 'Locating Background Information', 'Specialized encyclopedias offer starting points for research, and may include bibliographies that recommend further reading.<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1150}, {Dictionary of Italian Literature, 1996.},{01}}<br />\n{{dab},{1153}, {Encyclopedia of Italian Literary Studies, 2007.},{01}}<br />\n{{dab},{3}, {Literature Resource Center},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1151}, {Chambers Film Factfinder, 2006.},{01}}', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(449, 'Locating Articles', 'You&#39;ll have to distinguish between popular sources, often reviews of movies as they come out or are re-issued, and more scholarly or academic sources. &nbsp;Indexes of material on film often mix the two types of sources, popular and scholarly.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Generally, start with&nbsp;</strong><a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research">Summon</a>. &nbsp;This search tool looks in the full text of material available through Drew Library.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>For reviews of films:</strong><br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{76}, {LexisNexis Academic},{00}}<br />\nThis database provides full text of articles in Italian language newspapers, and is not well-covered in Summon. &nbsp;It has multiple internal divisions - make sure you&#39;re in the right one!<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/lexisnexis.png" style="width: 542px; height: 169px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;" /><br />\nThen, go to &quot;Advanced Options&quot; and select Italian:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/ln2.jpg" style="width: 505px; height: 355px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;" /><br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1152}, {MRQE (Movie Review Query Engine)},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n<strong>For academic articles:</strong><br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{40}, {MLA Bibliography},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{98}, {International Index to the Performing Arts},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{96}, {FIAF},{00}}<br />\nUse Index to Film Periodicals Plus to search for articles. &nbsp;Then use the list of films to search:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/FIAF.jpg" style="width: 508px; height: 320px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;" />', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
