(451, 'Scholary and literature review articles', '<strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">Identifying a scholarly journals/article:</strong>\n<ul style="padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px;">\n	<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; line-height: 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Identifying+Scholarly+Journals" target="_blank">Identify a scholarly article</a>&nbsp;</li>\n	<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; line-height: 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"><a href="http://unilearning.uow.edu.au/reading/1d.html" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" target="_blank">Strategies for reading journal articles.&nbsp;</a><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" />\n	Explains the basic structure of an academic articles.</li>\n</ul>\n<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">Reading scholarly articles:&nbsp;</strong>\n\n<ul style="padding-right: 0px; padding-left: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px;">\n	<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; line-height: 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 12.7272720336914px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"><a href="http://unilearning.uow.edu.au/reading/2c.html" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" target="_blank">Examples of critical reading.</a>&nbsp;<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" />\n	Real like examples of how to reading academic, popular and newspaper articles.</span></li>\n	<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; line-height: 20px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"><a href="http://unilearning.uow.edu.au/reading/2b.html" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" target="_blank">Strategies for reading journal articles - checklist</a>&nbsp;<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" />\n	&quot;These questions on this checklist&nbsp;are designed as a guide to the process of reading academic texts critically and analytically. You can apply these questions to most academic texts.&quot;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; line-height: 20px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"><br />\n<b>What is a literature review?</b></div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; line-height: 20px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"><a href="https://owl.english.purdue.edu/owl/resource/994/04/" target="_blank">Literature Reviews</a></li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
