(467, 'Identifying scholarly and popular articles ', 'When seeking sources, you will need to be able to determine whether or not an item is scholarly.<br />\n<br />\nRemember that while SUMMON and other databases will let you limit to peer reviewed journals, a given article can be non-scholarly in a scholarly journal.<br />\n<br />\nLinks below to check for help.\n<ul>\n	<li><a href="http://www.lib.ncsu.edu/tutorials/scholarly-popular/">Scholary and Popular Materials (LINK).</a>&nbsp; Excellent explanation of how to identify different sources with good graphics.&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">From NC State University Library.</span></li>\n	<li><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Identifying+Scholarly+Journals">Identifying Scholarly Journals (LINK)&nbsp;</a>&nbsp;Detailed guidelines for identifying scholarly and popular journals. From Drew University Library.</li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(468, 'Get full text', '<strong>Full text available&nbsp;</strong><br />\n<br />\nClick directly to the full text if available in a database, or click on &nbsp; <img src="http://depts.drew.edu/lib/AL_button.gif" />&nbsp; &nbsp;to find the full text in another database.The&nbsp;<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Drew+ArticleLinker" target="_blank">Article Linker guide</a>&nbsp;provides additional instructions for finding full text, either online or in print/microfilm format within the library.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Full text not available</strong><br />\n<br />\nDon&#39;t give up! &nbsp;There are other ways to get the information you are seeking.&nbsp;<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_mashmun/find_full_t.png" style="width: 468px; height: 582px;" /><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(469, 'Restricted summon search', '<script type="text/javascript" id="s080319a0c801013173da2ae8d1b2df50" src="http://drew.summon.serialssolutions.com/widgets/search.js" data-ajax-url="http://drew.summon.serialssolutions.com/widgets/search"></script><script type="text/javascript">new SummonSearchWidget({"id":"#s080319a0c801013173da2ae8d1b2df50","logo":"http://assets.summon.serialssolutions.com/4ff73479e8c1955a52000904","params":{"s.fvf[]":["IsFullText,true","ContentType,Newspaper Article,t"],"s.ho":["f"],"keep_r":true,"q":"medieval AND"},"style":{"link_color":"#1556e0","width":"fixed"},"title":"Medieval and ","searchbutton_text":"Search"})</script>', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(471, 'Choosing Terms and Combining Them', 'Especially when using a &#39;full text&#39; or &#39;natural language&#39; search, it&#39;s important to think about what terms to use.<br />\n<br />\nWhat different concepts are you interested in combining? One set of terms will define the type of behavior you&#39;re concerned about, the other the setting in which you&#39;re discussing it. So, for instance:<br />\nhomophobia in online gaming\n<ol>\n	<li>Concept 1: homophobia</li>\n	<li>Concept 2: online gaming</li>\n</ol>\n<br />\nYou also may want to consider different terms which may provide ways to get at the same concept, even if they are not synonyms For instance:\n<ol>\n	<li>online gaming, computer gaming, gamers,&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">World of Warcraft, Xbox Live</span></li>\n	<li>sports, athletics, games</li>\n	<li>classroom, schools, high school, elementary school, classes, education</li>\n	<li>gender-conforming, cisgender, stereotypically feminine or stereotypically masculine</li>\n	<li>homophobia, anti-homosexual</li>\n</ol>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(472, 'Searching SUMMON', 'Summon is a &#39;natural language&#39; search, which interprets your search terms in a way similar to Google&#39;s search function, and which includes information on as many as possible of all the resources the library has, from government documents to specific journal articles.<br />\n<br />\nNatural language searching may require you to try several different combinations of terms to get the best results to appear near the top. Though you can search on <b>combating homophobia in online gaming</b>, if you search on&nbsp;<strong>homophobia &quot;online gaming&quot;</strong> you get a different set of results. &nbsp;Once you have a set of results, typically a large one, you limit it down using the options on the left, just as you would when viewing an online shopping site:<br />\n&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jheise/revision.png" style="width: 688px; height: 451px;" />Special tools for Summon:<br />\n&quot;phrase search&quot; -- put a phrase inside of quotation marks<br />\n+required term -- put a + plus sign in front of a term that HAS to be in the results<br />\nAND and OR: use AND in all caps to combine two separate concepts; use OR in all caps to combine alternative concepts:&nbsp;<strong>transphobia AND sports&nbsp;</strong>;&nbsp;<strong>homophobia OR heterosexism</strong>', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(473, 'Interlibrary Loan', '<a class="external-link" href="http://screenr.com/xvis" rel="nofollow" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">Requesting an article through the ILLiad system</a><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<a class="external-link" href="http://screenr.com/Qfis" rel="nofollow" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">Requesting a book through the ILLiad system</a><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<a class="external-link" href="http://screenr.com/06is" rel="nofollow" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">Requesting an article directly from a database</a><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<a class="external-link" href="http://screenr.com/9vis" rel="nofollow" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(50, 108, 166); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">Requesting a book directly through Worldcat</a>', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(475, 'Google search tips', 'Find advocacy/interest groups on your topic by adding the following to your search terms in Google - site:org<br />\n<br />\nFind &nbsp;government information on your topic by adding the following to your &nbsp;search terms in Google - site:gov<br />\n<br />\nFind academic discussions on &nbsp;your topic by adding the following &nbsp;to your search terms in Google - &nbsp;site:edu', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(476, 'Search tips', '<strong>Connect</strong> parts of &nbsp;your topic by AND: dogs AND autism<br />\n<strong>Place</strong> quotation marks around phrases: &quot;therapy dogs&quot; AND autism<br />\n<strong>Separate</strong> synonyms with OR: &quot;therapy dog*&quot; OR &quot;service dog*&quot;<br />\n<strong>Use</strong> and asterix* to truncate words: thera* = therap, therapies, therapeutical<br />\n<strong>Place</strong> parentheses around search steps: (&quot;therapy dog* OR &quot;service dog*&quot;) AND autism', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
