(479, 'Summon search', '<h3 id="id-2014,Spring-WRTG115-CollegeWriting-Hart-SummonSearch" style="line-height: 1.5; margin: 30px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 12.7272720336914px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" target="_blank">Summon</a>&nbsp;is a google-like search of Drew Library Resources</strong>. You can look for books that are in the Drew Library with Summon, &nbsp;as well &nbsp;as academic (peer-reviewed or scholarly) &nbsp;articles, newspapers and &nbsp;other resources, such as vetted public websites.</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.7272720336914px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.7272720336914px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 12.7272720336914px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px;">Summon can be found on the Research Resources page. &nbsp;</span><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 12.7272720336914px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 20.8000011444092px;">From&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.drew.edu/home/" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; font-size: 12.7272720336914px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 20.8000011444092px;" target="_blank">Treehouse</a><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 12.7272720336914px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 20.8000011444092px;">, click on Research Resources:<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/research_resources.png" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: 122px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; width: 372px;" /><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" />\nType in keyword or phrase:<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/summon_crime_scene.png" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: 96px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; width: 509px;" /><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" />\nAfter searching, you will get lots of options to narrow &nbsp;your search. Some key limits are:</span></h3>\n\n<div style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 12.7272720336914px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px;">\n<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="filters" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0.7692em; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; vertical-align: top; border-spacing: 0px; zoom: 1; color: rgb(77, 77, 77); line-height: normal; background-color: rgb(230, 230, 230);">\n	<tbody class="static" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; zoom: 1;">\n		<tr style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; zoom: 1;">\n			<td class="facetLabel" style="padding: 2px 0px 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: top; zoom: 1;"><label for="facet:is_peer_reviewed" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; zoom: 1;"><span class="label" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 12px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; zoom: 1;">Limit to articles from peer-reviewed publications</span></label><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" />\n			<span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-size: 12px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">Book / eBook</span>\n\n			<div style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">&nbsp;</div>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/summon_filters.png" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: 543px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; width: 214px;" /><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" />\nThe more....button provides subtopics for your major topic. It&#39;s a very useful option because it helps to narrow your focus.</div>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(480, 'Get full text', '<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 10px 0px 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 20px;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">If there is no link to the full text:&nbsp;</span><img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/html_pdf.png" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: 36px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px; width: 379px;" /><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">&nbsp;click on the article linker icon:&nbsp;</span><img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/article_linker.png" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: 35px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px; width: 116px;" /><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">.</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">If the full tex is available from another database, you&#39;ll get a screen with hyperlinks to the article:</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/article_linker_results.png" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: 172px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px; width: 674px;" /><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">If there are no hyperlinks to an article, click on &quot;Request and InterLibrarLoan&quot;:</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/request_an_ILL.png" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: 124px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px; width: 364px;" /></p>\n\n<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 10px 0px 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 20px;"><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" />\nThe first time you request an article or book via InterLibraryLoan, you &nbsp;will &nbsp;be asked to fill out a short form.&nbsp;<b style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">It may take several days to receive an article via InterLibraryLoan; &nbsp;books can take longer.</b></p>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(481, 'More places to search', '<span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px;">From&nbsp;</span><a href="http://www.drew.edu/home/" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">Treehouse</a><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px;">, click on Research Resources:<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/treehouse_research_resources.png" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: 127px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; width: 363px;" /><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" />\nClick on List of Resources by Title (A-Z)<br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/a-z_list.png" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: 154px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; width: 496px;" /></span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;">Academic Search Premier is a good place to start your search. Also try ProQuest Research Library.</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/academic_search_premier.png" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: 469px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; font-size: 13px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 19.5px; width: 599px;" /><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(482, 'Table of Contents', '', NULL, 0, 'TOC', '{"ticked":"478,479,480,481,7,3"}', 0, 0, NULL),
(483, 'Demonstration', '<a href="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_mashmun/RFID_rights.pdf">Article 1</a><br />\n<br />\n<a href="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_mashmun/securityscramble.pdf">Article 2</a><br />\n<br />\n<a href="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_mashmun/journalofaccountancy.pdf">Article 3</a><br />\n<br />\n<a href="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_mashmun/publichealth.pdf">Article 4</a>', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(484, 'Choosing Terms and Combining Them', 'Especially when using a &#39;full text&#39; or &#39;natural language&#39; search, it&#39;s important to think about what terms to use.<br />\n<br />\nWhat different concepts are you interested in combining? One set of terms will define the type of behavior you&#39;re concerned about, the other the setting in which you&#39;re discussing it. So, for instance:<br />\nStreet art in New York City\n<ol>\n	<li>Concept 1: street art</li>\n	<li>Concept 2: New York City</li>\n</ol>\n<br />\nYou also may want to consider different terms which may provide ways to get at the same concept, even if they are not synonyms For instance:\n<ol>\n	<li>street art, graffiti, urban expression, mural arts</li>\n	<li>New York, New York City, NYC, Manhattan, Bronx, Queens, Brooklyn, Staten Island</li>\n	<li>urban, municipal, city, street</li>\n</ol>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(485, 'Get full text', '<strong>Full text available&nbsp;</strong><br />\n<br />\nClick directly to the full text if available in a database, or click on &nbsp; <img src="http://depts.drew.edu/lib/AL_button.gif" />&nbsp; &nbsp;to find the full text in another database.The&nbsp;<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Drew+ArticleLinker" target="_blank">Article Linker guide</a>&nbsp;provides additional instructions for finding full text, either online or in print/microfilm format within the library.<br />\n<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jheise/holdings.gif" style="width: 553px; height: 508px;" /><br />\n<br />\n<strong>Full text not available</strong><br />\n<br />\nDon&#39;t give up! &nbsp;There are other ways to get the information you are seeking.&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nIf the library does not have the item, use the Interlibrary Loan Request to request a copy of it; we&#39;ll get it from another library and post it to you online.', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(486, 'Searching Library Databases', 'In Academic Search Premier, you can search for New York City as a subject...<br />\nAnd limit to Scholarly (peer reviewed) article...<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jheise/asp-limits.gif" style="width: 466px; height: 322px;" />', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
