(527, 'Specific newspapers', 'In the database LexisNexis (access from<a href="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/subjects/databases.php?letter=L" target="_blank"> Database List L)</a>&nbsp;opt for the advanced search.<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/lexisnexis_advanced_options.png" style="width: 677px; height: 145px;" /><br />\n<br />\nStart typing the name of the newspaper into the Source box. If the newspaper is included in the database, you&#39;ll have the option to choose that newspaper. You can also limit your search by dates on this page also.<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/new_york_times.png" style="width: 423px; height: 336px;" /><br />\n<br />\nWant to know more about a newspaper? On the page that displays the &nbsp;full &nbsp;text of an article, &nbsp;near the top of the page there is an option to learn more about the newspaper. Click on &nbsp;the question mark icon to view this information.<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/lexisnexis_information_about_journal.png" style="width: 360px; height: 31px;" />', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(528, 'Articles and essays', 'Start with MLA bibliography, which is the primary index in literary criticism. &nbsp;After that, if necessary, check others according to your topic.<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{40}, {MLA Bibliography},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{96}, {FIAF},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{66}, {America History and Life},{01}}<br />\n{{dab},{74}, {Historical Abstracts},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{54}, {Women&#39;s Studies International},{01}}<br />\n<br />\nTwo additional resources that provide access to a very wide range of material:<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{18}, {Google Scholar},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{2}, {SUMMON},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(529, 'Books and dissertations', '{{dab},{16}, {Drew Library Catalog},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{197}, {Dissertations and Theses},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{94}, {Worldcat},{01}}', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(530, 'Does Drew Own It?', '<strong>For articles:</strong><br />\nWhen you have found them within a database, click on&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/ArticleLinker.jpg" style="width: 72px; height: 18px;" /> to find the full text, if it is not available within the database.<br />\n<br />\nWhen you have a citation, either search for the article title and author in Summon, OR check the <a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/journals">Journal List Search</a>&nbsp;for the title of the journal.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>For books:</strong><br />\nCheck the <a href="https://librarycat.drew.edu/">Drew Library Catalog</a> If Drew does not own or have access to the item, request it through <a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/interlibrary-loan-request">Interlibrary Loan</a>. &nbsp;If you are currently searching a database, when you click on&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/ArticleLinker.jpg" style="width: 72px; height: 18px;" />, there will be an option for Interlibrary Loan. &nbsp;Click on that, and your item will be pasted into the Interlibrary Loan form.<br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(531, 'Citation Manual', 'The Modern Language Association published two guides that include sections on formatting notes and bibliographies:<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{916}, {MLA Handbook for Writers of Research Papers},{01}}Less complete than the Style Manual, but more user-friendly.<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{917}, {MLA Style Manual and Guide to Scholarly Publishing},{01}}<br />\n<br />\nFor summaries of formats, check:<br />\n{{dab},{316}, {MLA Formatting and Style Guide &ndash; The OWL at Purdue},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1045}, {EndnoteWeb},{01}} &nbsp;For help in using, check Drew&#39;s <a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Endnote+Web+Bibliographic+Software">guide</a>.', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(533, 'Books and Dissertations', '{{dab},{16}, {Drew Library Catalog},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{197}, {Dissertations and Theses},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{94}, {Worldcat},{01}}', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(534, 'Articles and Essays', '<strong>Start with MLA bibliography</strong>, which is the primary index in literary criticism. &nbsp;After that, if necessary, check others according to your topic.<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{40}, {MLA Bibliography},{01}}<br />\nBegin with a natural-language search, and identify the subject terms that best describe your topic:<br />\n(image with women and tennyson --&gt; Gender politics in alfred lord tennyson. . . )<br />\nIn MLA, it&#39;s also possible to specify the <b>author</b> and the&nbsp;<strong>work</strong> you want to focus on, by selecting from the drop-down menu &quot;Primary Subject<br />\nAuthor&quot; or &quot;Primary Subject Work.&quot;<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{96}, {FIAF},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{66}, {America History and Life},{01}}<br />\n{{dab},{74}, {Historical Abstracts},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{54}, {Women&#39;s Studies International},{01}}<br />\n<br />\nTwo additional resources that provide access to a very wide range of material:<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{18}, {Google Scholar},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{2}, {SUMMON},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Finding full text:</strong><br />\nCheck Drew&#39;s guide to <a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Finding+Periodicals">Finding Periodicals</a>&nbsp;for instructions on finding full text of articles. &nbsp;You can also use Summon - enter the title of the article (in quotation marks) and the author. &nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nIf you&#39;re looking for an essay in a book, check the <a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/catalog">Drew Catalog</a>. &nbsp;&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(536, 'Background', '<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Although course readings often provide sufficient context, it can be useful to consult specialized encyclopedias, which provide overviews of theories, events, authors or works. &nbsp;Always check for bibliographies at the end of the entries - they have been compiled as recommended starting points by the entry&#39;s author, who can be an expert on the topic</span><br />\n<br />\n<b>Literary Theory:</b><br />\n{{dab},{1058}, {Edinburgh encyclopedia of modern criticism and theory, 2002},{01}}<br />\n{{dab},{1085}, {Encyclopedia of Contemporary Literary Theory, 1993.},{00}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1082}, {Encyclopedia of Literary and Cultural Theory, 2011.},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1083}, {Johns Hopkins Guide to Literary Theory &amp; Criticism, 2005.},{01}}<br />\n{{dab},{1084}, {Key Concepts in Postcolonial LIterature},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Literature and Authors:</strong><br />\n{{dab},{42}, {Literature Criticism Online},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{3}, {Literature Resource Center},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1086}, {New Literary History of America, 2009},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{121}, {Oxford Encyclopedia of American Literature},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{122}, {Oxford Encyclopedia of British Literature},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Social Context:</strong><br />\n{{dab},{1168}, {Encyclopedia of the Victorian Era, 2004.},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1169}, {Reader&#39;s Guide to British History, 2003.},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1167}, {Companion to British History},{00}}<br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(537, 'Formatting Your Paper', '{{dab},{916}, {MLA Handbook for Writers of Research Papers},{01}}<br />\n{{dab},{917}, {MLA Style Manual and Guide to Scholarly Publishing},{01}}<br />\n{{dab},{316}, {MLA Formatting and Style Guide &ndash; The OWL at Purdue},{01}}A user-friendly guide to MLA basics.<br />\n<br />\nDrew Library has a citation software, EndNote Web, which can collect citations from databases, format bibliographies according to various styles, and maintain links to the full text of articles. &nbsp;For more information, check Drew&#39;s <a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Endnote+Web+Bibliographic+Software">Guide to EndNote Web</a>, or contact Jenne Heise (jheise@drew.edu, 973-408-3675).', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(539, 'What if Drew Doesn''t Own It?', 'If Drew does not own or have access to some material, you can request an Interlibrary Loan. &nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nIf you discover through the <img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/ArticleLinker.jpg" style="width: 72px; height: 18px;" /> results that we don&#39;t hold something, click on Interlibrary Loan, and the form will be filled out:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/LinkerScreen.jpg" style="width: 319px; height: 252px;" /><br />\nThe first time you use Interlibrary Loan, you will have to set up an ILLiad account with your Drew username and password.<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(544, 'Table of Contents', '', NULL, 0, 'TOC', '{"ticked":"528,529,530,531,3,6,7"}', 0, 0, NULL),
(546, 'Data', '<a href="http://data.un.org/" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">UNdata</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;">&nbsp;-</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;">A single entry point for UN statistical databases.</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<a href="http://unstats.un.org/unsd/default.htm" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">United Nations Statistics Division</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;">&nbsp;-</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;">Access Social and Demographic statistics, and the Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade)</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\nW<a href="http://www.app.collinsindicate.com/worldbankatlas-global/en" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">orld Bank eAtlas of Global Development</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;">&nbsp;-</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;">The World Bank eAtlas of Global Development maps and graphs more than 175 thematically organized indicators for over 200 countries, letting you visualize and compare progress on the most important development challenges facing our world. Most indicators cover several decades, so you can see, for example, how &ldquo;life expectancy at birth&rdquo; has improved from 1960 up through the latest year.</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<a href="https://openknowledge.worldbank.org/" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">World Bank &ndash; Open Knowledge Repository</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;">&nbsp;</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<a href="http://www.who.int/topics/en/" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">WHO &ndash; Health topics</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;">&nbsp;-</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;">International statistics and information on mental health worldwide.</span><br style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;" />\n<a href="http://www.imf.org/external/index.htm" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); text-decoration: none; font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">I</a><a href="http://data.imf.org/?sk=7CB6619C-CF87-48DC-9443-2973E161ABEB" target="_blank">MF eLibrary Data</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;"><a href="http://data.imf.org/?sk=7CB6619C-CF87-48DC-9443-2973E161ABEB" target="_blank">&nbsp;</a>-The IMF is an organization of 184 countries, working to foster global monetary cooperation, secure financial stability, facilitate international trade, promote high employment and sustainable economic growth, and reduce poverty. Search by dataset or data topic.</span><br />\n<a href="http://www.womanstats.org/" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(85, 26, 139); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;" target="_blank">WomanStats Project</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13.3333330154419px; line-height: 19.5px;">&nbsp;-&nbsp;Provides information on the status of women worldwide.</span><br />\n{{dab},{57}, {Statistical DataSets},{01}}<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(548, 'Scholarly articles', 'Use Summon and use the limit for &quot;Limit to articles from peer reviewed publications.<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/summon_women_migration.png" style="width: 850px; height: 630px;" /><br />\nUse a more subject specific database, linked from <a href="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/subjects/databases.php" target="_blank">Resources by Title</a>&nbsp;Relevant databases include:\n<ul>\n	<li>EconLit</li>\n	<li>SocIndex</li>\n	<li>Academic &nbsp;Search Premier</li>\n	<li>Business Source Elite</li>\n	<li>Gender Watch</li>\n	<li>Women&#39;s Studies International</li>\n</ul>\nMake &nbsp;sure to limit your results to Scholarly/Peer reviewed/Academic articles<br />\n<br />\nTry a <a href="https://scholar.google.com/" target="_blank">Google Scholar </a>search.<br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(549, 'Books', 'The best way to search for books in the Drew Catalog is through the <a href="https://librarycat.drew.edu/web2/tramp2.exe/goto/A03gfadu.000?screen=searchexact.html" target="_blank">Exact</a> search.<br />\nUse the dropdown menu and select <strong>subject.&nbsp;</strong>Type in your subject keyword.<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_epatters/catalog_exact_women.png" style="width: 435px; height: 69px;" /><br />\nSome appropriate keywords include: women; feminism; globalization.<br />\nChose an apopropriate subtopic from the resulting list OR scroll/page through subtopics to find the best match for your research focus (subtopics are listed alphabetically, so paging through this list is necessary.<br />\n<br />\nAlso consider doing a keyword search in<a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research" target="_blank"> Summon</a> (Summon does a google-like search of the Library&#39;s &nbsp;resources).<br />\nUse the limits on &nbsp;the left hand side of the search results page to focus your search.<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(550, 'Table of Contents', '', NULL, 0, 'TOC', '{"ticked":"548,549,546,7,564,551,3"}', 0, 0, NULL),
(551, 'InterLibraryLoan', 'Need an article or book Drew doesn&#39;t own or provide online access to?<br />\n<a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/about/services/ill" target="_blank">Use InterLibraryLoan</a><br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(552, 'Citation help', '<strong style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Electronic citation managment</strong><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">{{dab},{1045}, {EndnoteWeb},{11}}</span><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">(Beware: No citation software is perfect--check your work!) &nbsp;</span><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Endnote+Web+Bibliographic+Software" style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" target="_blank">Instructions for EndNote Web</a>\n<ul>\n	<li>Upcoming workshops: check&nbsp;<a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/2016/01/endnote-webbasic-training-feb-22-24">HERE</a></li>\n</ul>\n<strong><span style="font-size: 13px;">Reference Books&nbsp;</span></strong><br />\n<span style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">Lipson, Charles.&nbsp;</span><i style="zoom: 1; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">Doing Honest Work in College: How to Prepare Citations, Avoid Plagiarism, and Achieve Real Academic Success</i><span style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: normal;">. Chicago: University of Chicago Press, 2004. Print .</span><span style="font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-align: -webkit-center; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">PN171 .F56 L56 2004</span><br />\n<br />\n<strong>Reference Librarians</strong><br />\nContact Margery Ashmun or the Reference Librarian at the Library&#39;s Research Help Desk for assistance with formatting citations.<strong> &nbsp;</strong><br />\n<br />\n<strong style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Drew University&#39;s plagiarism policy</strong><br style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;" />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.7999992370605px;">Take time to familiarize yourself with Drew&#39;s policy on plagiarism. &nbsp;<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Handbook/Academic+Integrity+policy" target="_blank">CLICK HERE</a>&nbsp;for a link to&nbsp;the &quot;Academic Integrity&quot; section of Drew&#39;s Student Handbook which&nbsp;contains a&nbsp;description of the plagiarism policy.</span>', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(553, 'Get full text', '<strong>Full text available&nbsp;</strong><br />\nClick directly to the full text if available in a database, or click on &nbsp; <img src="http://depts.drew.edu/lib/AL_button.gif" />&nbsp; &nbsp;to find the full text in another database.The&nbsp;<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/Library/Drew+ArticleLinker" target="_blank">Article Linker guide</a>&nbsp;provides additional instructions for finding full text, either online or in print/microfilm format within the library.<br />\n<strong>Full text not available</strong><br />\nDon&#39;t give up! &nbsp;There are other ways to get the information you are seeking.&nbsp;<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_mashmun/find_full_t.png" style="width: 468px; height: 582px;" /><br />\nContact me via email or telephone at the Library if you are having trouble locating full text, mashmun@drew.edu or 973-408-3483.&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
