(860, 'Tips for Google Searching', '<ul>\n	<li>Use the Advanced Search</li>\n	<li>Use double quotes for exact phrases: &quot;social media marketing&quot;</li>\n	<li>Use the asterisk inside double quotes for a missing term: &quot;devil in a * dress&quot;</li>\n	<li>To require a particular term, prefix it with the plus sign +: &nbsp;&quot;chronicles of narnia&quot; discussion questions +college</li>\n	<li>To exclude ALL references to a particular term, prefix it with the minus sign -&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>search for definitions: Define:[term]</li>\n	<li>Math: type in your mathematical equation.</li>\n	<li>Conversions: [number] [unit] in [another unit]: &nbsp;23 teaspoons in cups</li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(861, 'Google Images Tips', '<ul>\n	<li>images.google.com</li>\n	<li>Search by image (upload an image or use a URL)</li>\n	<li>Limit by re-use rights</li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(862, 'Finding Articles and Books', '<strong>To find articles</strong>, check one of the following databases, all of which have features that will make your results more focused than Google or even Summon would. &nbsp;Pick a database on the basis of its subject focus:<br />\n<br />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;">​</span><span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;">{{dab},{66}, {America History and Life},{01}} &nbsp;To restrict your search to a specific time period, use the &quot;Historical Period&quot; limits on the first screen.</span><br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{71}, {Ethnic Newswatch},{01}} &nbsp;This database includes a mix of popular and scholarly material. &nbsp;To limit your search to a specific ethnicity, select the appropriate group under &quot;Ethnic Group&quot; on the first screen.<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{40}, {MLA Bibliography},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n<strong>To find books</strong>, check the&nbsp;{{dab},{16}, {Drew Library Catalog},{00}}. &nbsp;Use separate search boxes to search for the component concepts in your topic:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/catalog.jpg" style="width: 297px; height: 98px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;" /><br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(863, 'Finding Background Material', 'To develop a broad sense of the American ethnic experience, checking an encyclopedia will provide more solid information than Wikipedia. &nbsp;One of the following might be helpful:<br />\n<br />\n<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 20.8px;">{{dab},{1315}, {Encyclopedia of American Studies, 2014},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1316}, {Encyclopedia of African-American Culture and History, 2006},{01}}</span><br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1314}, {Encyclopedia of Race, Ethnicity and Society, 2008.},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{114}, {Oxford Encyclopedia of Latinos and Latinas in the United States},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(864, 'Formatting Citations', 'Purdue&#39;s <a href="https://owl.english.purdue.edu/owl/resource/747/01/">Online Writing Lab (OWL)</a> has a helpful set of guides to MLA format.<br />\n<br />\nDrew University also supports Endnote, a formatting software that helps you manage your bibliographies and citations:<br />\n<br />\n<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/x/JwHy">How to use Endnote Basic/Endnote Web</a><br />\n&nbsp;\n<ul style="margin: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 253, 246);">\n	<li><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Endnote+Web+-+Signing+up+for+an+Account" style="color: rgb(59, 115, 175); text-decoration: none;">Endnote Web - Signing up for an Account</a></li>\n	<li><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Entering+Your+Own+Citations+in+EndnoteWeb" style="color: rgb(59, 115, 175); text-decoration: none;">Entering Your Own Citations in EndnoteWeb</a></li>\n	<li><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Sharing+your+Endnote+References+with+your+instructor" style="color: rgb(59, 115, 175); text-decoration: none;">Sharing your Endnote References with your instructor</a></li>\n	<li><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Emailing+References+from+Endnote+Basic" style="color: rgb(59, 115, 175); text-decoration: none;">Emailing References from Endnote Basic</a></li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
