(964, 'Contact Information', 'I often staff the Library Reference Desk, but meetings in my office are ideal. You can <a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/ask-a-librarian">schedule an appointment during my formal office hours</a> Tuesday 9am-1pm, but <strong>walk-ins are welcome at any time</strong> during the week. &nbsp; Appointments by email are perhaps most advantageous. Make an appointment by containing me at <a href="mailto:rmikulski@drew.edu">rmikulski@drew.edu</a> or 973.408.3480', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(965, 'Endnote Resources', '<a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/x/JwHy">How to use Endnote Basic/Endnote Web</a><br />\n&nbsp;\n<ul style="margin: 0px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 253, 246);">\n	<li><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Endnote+Web+-+Signing+up+for+an+Account" style="color: rgb(59, 115, 175); text-decoration: none;">Endnote Web - Signing up for an Account</a></li>\n	<li><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Entering+Your+Own+Citations+in+EndnoteWeb" style="color: rgb(59, 115, 175); text-decoration: none;">Entering Your Own Citations in EndnoteWeb</a></li>\n	<li><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Sharing+your+Endnote+References+with+your+instructor" style="color: rgb(59, 115, 175); text-decoration: none;">Sharing your Endnote References with your instructor</a></li>\n	<li><a href="https://uknow.drew.edu/confluence/display/techdocs/Emailing+References+from+Endnote+Basic" style="color: rgb(59, 115, 175); text-decoration: none;">Emailing References from Endnote Basic</a></li>\n</ul>\n', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(966, 'Finding 19th-Century Sources', 'To locate material from the 19th-century, start with an index. &nbsp;Indexes may or may not have the full text of the items, but they will identify where the text was originally published. &nbsp;Check the {{dab},{16}, {Drew Library Catalog},{00}}&nbsp;or the <a href="http://www.drew.edu/library/research/journals">Journal List Search</a> to see if Drew holds the material - if we don&#39;t, request it through&nbsp;{{dab},{1123}, {InterLibrary Loan},{00}}.<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{120}, {Nineteenth Century Masterfile},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{1369}, {Wellesley Index to Victorian Periodicals, 1824-1900},{01}}<br />\n<br />\n{{dab},{94}, {Worldcat},{00}}<br />\nYou can either search for your topic and the&nbsp;<strong>subject term</strong>&nbsp;<em>sources</em>, or restrict the publication date:<br />\n<img alt="" src="http://walter.drew.edu/splus/assets/users/_jcaldwel/WorldCat19th.jpg" style="width: 633px; height: 300px; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;" /><br />\n&nbsp;', NULL, 0, 'Basic', '', 0, 0, NULL),
