(1341, 'Linus Pauling and the Nature of the Chemical Bond: A Documentary History', '', 'Easy to navigate website offers the biography of the chemist Linus Pauling and the history of the nature of the chemical bond. This website offers access to materials in different formats, e.g. audio, video, manuscripts and photos. Primary resources include correspondence between Pauling and other notable scientists of his time, e.g. Schrodinger and Heisenberg. Information regarding the research that led to Pauling&rsquo;s 1954 Nobel Prize in Chemistry is highly browsable.From the Special Collections &nbsp;&amp; Archives Research Center at the Valley Library, Oregon State University.', '', NULL, '2015-12-01 22:32:18', 0),
(1342, 'Merck Manual (Online)', '', 'An online medical reference with two options for content delivery: (1) a professional version that provides more advanced information for healthcare professionals and students or (2) a consumer version that offers easier-to-interpret content for readers who may be patients or caregivers. The professional version segments information into &quot;Medical Topics&quot;, &quot;Drug Information&quot;, &quot;News &amp; Commentary&quot;, &quot;Procedures &amp; Exams&quot;, and more. Topics are often covered in brief, usually with links to the supporting scholarly research in peer-reviewed journals that require a subscription.', '', NULL, '2015-12-07 21:16:00', 0),
(1343, 'The Immanent Frame', '', 'A digital project created in conjunction with the Religion and the Public Sphere program of the Social Science Research Council.', '', NULL, '2015-12-15 19:15:14', 0),
